text = '[{"id":"b244f354-948a-11e6-827c-2253b130d742","created_at":"Mon Oct 17 16:57:25 UTC 2016","title":"Senior iOS Engineer","location":"Mountain View, Ca","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Are you a Swift-writing savant determined to make every mobile experience you craft the best it can be? Yes? You\u2019re in luck! Because we\u2019re looking for a seasoned iOS engineer to help make the SmugMug Mobile app experience be all it can be\u2014and better. You\u2019ll have the opportunity to play a big part in a small team, developing mobile apps and defining their platform. Work closely with other iOS and Android engineers as well as designers, product managers, and other stakeholders to build the best mobile experience out there.. </p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Own significant portions of applications from concept through deployment and support</li>\n<li>Participate in the entire design and development process, collaborating with design, marketing, QA, and PMs</li>\n<li>Act as a resource for your direct development responsibilities and for iOS and Swift codebases in general</li>\n<li>Mentor and provide guidance to junior engineers</li>\n<li>Monitor new technologies and opportunities to expand existing applications or define new ones</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Must haves</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience developing iOS applications from concept through post-launch support</li>\n<li>Experience with Swift</li>\n<li>Experience with networking libraries and consuming JSON/RESTful APIs</li>\n<li>Great understanding of memory management</li>\n<li>Comfortable with asynchronous programming using GCD</li>\n<li>Good understanding of \u201cperceived performance\u201d and maintaining a responsive UI</li>\n<li>Experience with View and ViewController programming using xibs</li>\n<li>Ability to set own timelines and expectations</li>\n<li>Flexibility to get things done quickly or well-architected as needed and the ability to recognize when to do which</li>\n<li>Can work from high-level concepts and sketches as pixel-perfect mockups</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Nice to haves</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Git and Github</li>\n<li>Multi-threaded CoreData</li>\n<li>Understanding of Protocol Oriented Programming</li>\n<li>Use of ViewModels or MVVM in general</li>\n<li>Integration testing</li>\n<li>Developing frameworks and SDKs</li>\n<li>Managing performant file I/O for image and metadata files</li>\n<li>Image-related frameworks (ALAssets, Core Graphics)</li>\n<li>Passion for photography</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"http://jobs.smugmug.com/Open-Positions/Senior-iOS-Engineer\">http://jobs.smugmug.com/Open-Positions/Senior-iOS-Engineer</a></p>\n","company":"SmugMug","company_url":"http://www.smugmug.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/0664b98e-948a-11e6-9924-6897f47dcd54.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/b244f354-948a-11e6-827c-2253b130d742"},{"id":"2426ebf6-e641-11e5-8030-461e4e18f3ad","created_at":"Mon Oct 17 15:16:37 UTC 2016","title":"Experienced Backend Engineer","location":"Remote","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><a href=\"https://citrusbyte.com\">Citrusbyte</a> is a software development company which believes in using simple tools to solve all types of problems. We work closely with designers, engineers and our clients to create and improve products of great quality. We have considerable experience building custom systems for both startups and enterprises - check out our <a href=\"https://citrusbyte.com/portfolio\">portfolio</a> for more information about our clients.</p>\n\n<p>We strongly advocate minimalism and this is represented in the tools we choose to work with. Every team gets to decide their own stack depending on the requirements of the project.</p>\n\n<p>Our main offices are in Los Angeles and New York, but we work remotely with people from all around the world.</p>\n\n<p>Our engineers have experience in a consultative environment, excellent communication skills and a desire to work with talented teams building innovative products. We work closely with our clients, sharing our experience to help them better define their products.</p>\n\n<p>Most of our projects are written in <strong>Ruby</strong>, so experience in this language is required.</p>\n\n<p>We believe that less is more and value simplicity above all else. This is reflected in the tools we choose to work with. For this reason we tend to avoid using big frameworks like Rails and instead use smaller tools like Sinatra, Roda or Cuba.</p>\n\n<p>We have also done projects in Node.js, Go, Python, Lua, etc. And strive to learn new tools and languages everyday. We believe in always choosing the right tool for the job and we are very open minded about trying different technologies.</p>\n\n<h3>Skills &amp; Requirements:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Smart, gets things done.</li>\n<li>Passionate about software development.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication / consulting experience.</li>\n<li>Open minded and always learning</li>\n<li>Experience working in a distributed company</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Duties &amp; Responsibilities:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Architect and build web applications.</li>\n<li>Work with product designers and clients to clarify requirements.</li>\n<li>Plan and prioritize work in a collaborative remote team.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>You can apply directly on our <a href=\"http://careers.citrusbyte.com/apply/tPTZOv/Experienced-Backend-Engineer\">careers page</a></p>\n","company":"Citrusbyte","company_url":"https://citrusbyte.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/f9c13b32-e640-11e5-9749-ea3708a49aac.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/2426ebf6-e641-11e5-8030-461e4e18f3ad"},{"id":"88ba13d2-9478-11e6-9003-5b891a89d8b5","created_at":"Mon Oct 17 14:47:32 UTC 2016","title":"Execution Developer","location":"Radnor, PA. USA","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Stevens Capital Management LP (\u201cSCM\u201d) is a registered investment adviser that manages a multi-billion dollar hedge fund that has been in business for 25+ years.</p>\n\n<p>SCM specializes in the rigorous development and disciplined implementation of empirically based quantitative trading strategies. Our highly productive team works in a fast-paced collegial environment, utilizing extensive data sets, technology and the scientific method to devise and employ trading strategies throughout the world\u2019s most liquid financial markets.</p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re seeking highly driven, production-oriented developers who possess strong technical skills and the ability to work in a fast-paced collaborative environment.  </p>\n\n<p>Primary Responsibilities</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and support multi-threaded applications with a strong emphasis on high performance.</li>\n<li>Optimize our multi-faceted low latency global trade execution platform using network and systems programming.</li>\n<li>Create tools to process, store and analyze quote and order data.</li>\n<li>Work closely with our quantitative research analysts, engineers and other groups to provide software solutions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Requirements</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A minimum of three years professional-level C++ programming experience in a Linux environment. </li>\n<li>A Computer Science or Mathematics degree.</li>\n<li>Outstanding problem solving skills.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of shell scripts and other languages including Java, Python or Perl is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Please submit your resume to: \n<a href=\"mailto:recruiting@scm-lp.com\">recruiting@scm-lp.com</a></p>\n","company":"Stevens Capital Management LP","company_url":"http://www.scm-lp.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/812b1ca6-9478-11e6-9056-6d7b50fd388a.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/88ba13d2-9478-11e6-9003-5b891a89d8b5"},{"id":"5bbed65c-9472-11e6-9195-1bbe84df1fd2","created_at":"Mon Oct 17 14:05:27 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Backend Developer (PHP)","location":"Amsterdam or Rotterdam","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><b>You are a technically curious Backend PHP Developer that wants to be part of a core development product team. You do understand (and maybe even have already harvested) the power of things like TDD, DDD, CQRS ? Then apply for the position of Senior Backend Developer (PHP) at VONQ and be part of our team that builds our flagship product, tools and APIs that serve global customers! #gettingthingsdoneright</b></p>\n\n<p><b>Senior Backend Developer (PHP)</b><br>\nRotterdam and / or Amsterdam, fulltime position (32 - 40)\nYou can be based either in Amsterdam or Rotterdam. The choice is yours!</p>\n\n<p><b>Description</b></p>\n\n<p>As a Senior Backend Developer in the VONQ Product Team, you will be leading critical product development efforts and get your hands dirty in the implementation of our revised core platform. You&#39;ll be working closely with our CTO and our product development. You will be developing new product offerings, improve existing ones, roll out products to production and ensure all works well in our DTAP. Key to success is automation. Together we will be paving the path to Continuous Delivery.</p>\n\n<p><b>What you actually will do</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Contribute to development process improvements through tools and automation and proper DTAP environment setup (working close to our devops engineer)</li>\n<li>Contribute to design and implementation of scalable and performing production</li>\n<li>Contribute to design and development of revised application platform on basis of big data technologies that fit current and future data usage scenarios (think of ELK stack)</li>\n<li>Lead design and implementation efforts of core applications, APIs and services</li>\n<li>Mentor team members</li>\n<li>Safe-guard enterprise product quality of APIs and GUIs</li>\n<li>Strengthen environment, data &amp; application security</li>\n<li>Realize a path to Continuous Delivery</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Which boxes do you tick?</b><br>\n(Psst...You do not need to tick all the boxes below in order to apply...)\nWhat you see below, paints the ideal picture. Obviously, we also work well with people that have appetite to excel, foundation to build on and potential to succeed.</p>\n\n<p>If things below are in your bucket list and dying to put your hands into, then do Apply!</p>\n\n<p><i>&quot;Our perfect picture&quot;:</i></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor degree or equivalent relevant work experience</li>\n<li>Experience with Agile methodologies (Scrum / Kanban)</li>\n<li>Product development experience - knowing what it takes to build a future-proof product...</li>\n<li>Fan and evangelizer of solid development practices (TDD, CI etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience with rolling out products to production (incl. proper version mngt)</li>\n<li>Experience leading development efforts and aligning with FE engineers &amp; Data designers</li>\n<li>Have worked before in distributed team is a plus</li>\n<li>Love to code (weapons of choice: Symfony, phpunit and phpspec for testing are in your armory)</li>\n<li>You see beauty in engineering (event sourcing, CQRS, event driven design, scalable architectures)</li>\n<li>Experience with solid API design is a big plus</li>\n<li>Experience working with Relational and non-Relational (NoSQL) Databases;</li>\n<li>Experience with scalable reporting solutions is a plus (think of Logstash / ElasticSearch / Kibana)</li>\n<li>Experience with multilayer application design &amp; integrations and dependencies management</li>\n<li>Experience with TDD and end\u2013to-end testing is plus</li>\n<li>Experience with data visualization projects is a big plus</li>\n<li>Experience with data driven products is a big plus</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills in English</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Things we cherish</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Business-focus</li>\n<li>Entrepreneurial spirit</li>\n<li>Technical curiosity, critically open to new tools and technologies</li>\n<li>Caring for good, extensible architecture across board</li>\n<li>Good communicator (in English)</li>\n<li>Pragmatism</li>\n<li>Goal driven personality</li>\n<li>Lame jokes (what can I say...) &amp; beer on Fridays and often BBQs at our terrace ;-)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>What\u2019s in it for you</b><br>\nFirst of all, you\u2019ll be working with experienced colleagues with a strong vision on web development and software architecture, giving you a full intellectual challenge every day. Secondly, every two weeks you\u2019ll have dedicated R&amp;D time to move the development of our Job Marketing Platform to the next level. Thirdly, you&#39;ll participate to meetups/conferences.</p>\n\n<p><b>What\u2019s more</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Laptop of your preferences and two extra screens on your desk</li>\n<li>Flexible working hours</li>\n<li>Time and budget for training</li>\n<li>5 weeks paid holiday per year</li>\n<li>Good salary and additional incentives</li>\n<li>Fixed term contract with an option for perm</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>So, does this sounds appealing to you?</b><br>\nPlease apply by clicking on this <a href=\"https://vonq.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/senior_backend_developer_php_rotterdam/116075/V819/apply\">\u200blink\u200b</a>\u200b</p>\n\n<p>If you have any questions, please send an e-mail to Dimitra Retsina (CTO/CPO) -&gt; dimitra(at)vonq.com.</p>\n\n<p><b>About VONQ &amp; Job Marketing Platform</b><br>\nYou will be contributing to our flagship product called Job Marketing Platform (JMP). It\u2019s a (big) data-driven application with a recommendation engine to serve multiple personas. JMP incorporates the team\u2019s learnings and best practices including CQRS and event sourcing. Although it\u2019s a young product we\u2019re practicing LEAN methodology to gradually evolve it in a modular way and having a very ambitious roadmap in mind.</p>\n\n<p><i>Keywords: PHP, product Engineer, Symfony, CQRS, big dat</i></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://vonq.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/senior_backend_developer_php_rotterdam/116075/V819/apply\">Click here to apply!</A></p>\n","company":"VONQ","company_url":"https://www.vonq.com/nl/","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/db7c6590-9471-11e6-9d0f-9ee8b0c45a9e.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/5bbed65c-9472-11e6-9195-1bbe84df1fd2"},{"id":"66ef8ce4-946b-11e6-9324-b307ae72ab81","created_at":"Mon Oct 17 13:13:11 UTC 2016","title":"Lead PHP Engineer","location":"London","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Our Client, Arqiva,  are an international broadcast operator who specialize in distribution and connectivity for well known content owners.</p>\n\n<p>They are looking to for a Lead PHP Software Engineer, to provide hands on technical leadership to their backend development team in their Central London office.</p>\n\n<p>Working within the connect solutions division, the position will involve developing functionality and features for Freeview EPGs (Electronic programme guides) for UK TV channels.</p>\n\n<p>Leading a team of two PHP developers, the Lead Engineer will be responsible for writing clean testable code while encouraging best development practices, and working closely with the platform architects. Fluency in PHP and PHPUnit, combined with a high level understanding of RESTful services, XML and Symfony2 are essential. Previous management and leadership experience is also beneficial. </p>\n\n<p>The freeview EPG is used by millions of viewers across the country every day and is an essential part of the freeview user experience. This is a great opportunity to join a leading provider of smart solutions, currently shaping the future of the broadcast industry. </p>\n\n<p>This position is office hours, Monday-Friday, and spec&#39;d with a salary of up to \u00a365k (dependent on experience), and comes with excellent benefits package.</p>\n\n<p>Skills Needed:\n(Required) PHP and PHPUnit\n(Required) RESTful services\n(High) Symfony2\n(High) XML and XSD\n(Medium) Linux\n(Medium) GIT\n(Low) Docker/Containers</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>email your CV to <a href=\"mailto:getintouch@frame-25.com\">getintouch@frame-25.com</a></p>\n","company":"Frame 25","company_url":"http://www.frame-25.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/619613bc-946b-11e6-986e-84fc281b563a.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/66ef8ce4-946b-11e6-9324-b307ae72ab81"},{"id":"180a1f84-9274-11e6-95c9-9a48662d1572","created_at":"Sat Oct 15 01:11:27 UTC 2016","title":"Full Stack Engineer","location":"New York, NY","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Noom\u2019s applications combat chronic and pre-chronic conditions with structured programs and human coaches. Our technology engages users and improves health outcomes by combining the best technologies and human coaching in a single powerful platform. Coaches are given a detailed dashboard of the data our users provide in Noom Health, thus giving them the information necessary to help our users reach their health goals, whether it\u2019s to lower their blood sugar and sodium, lose weight, or prevent Type-II Diabetes or Hypertension. The full stack engineer we are seeking will be a core contributor to the development of our coaching tools platform and dashboard app. Their goal is to ultimately increase the efficiency and effectiveness of our coaches, allowing them to make smarter and more impactful recommendations when working with our user base.</p>\n\n<p>What We\u2019re Looking For:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>1- 4 years of full stack web development experience in Django, node.js, Rails, or something similar </li>\n<li>Experience with, and interest in, Javascript, React (or backbone.js, angular.js, ember.js), Python, HTML5, CSS </li>\n<li>Good communicator: comfortable explaining technical problems in person and in writing </li>\n<li>Team player: has fun learning and sharing new concepts, and enjoys collaborating with a team </li>\n<li>Rock-solid coding skills: writes code that is well structured, idiomatic, reusable, and easy to understand </li>\n<li>They should own what they do, and not just throw code out. Sense of responsibility and ownership. They would have to come from an environment in which people are responsible for their own code </li>\n<li>Has developed and shipped a dynamic web app successfully in a team environment</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"http://grnh.se/1687oq1\">http://grnh.se/1687oq1</a></p>\n","company":"Noom","company_url":"http://www.noom.com","company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/180a1f84-9274-11e6-95c9-9a48662d1572"},{"id":"4f0531ae-9265-11e6-9b6e-cd45403bef14","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 23:24:09 UTC 2016","title":"CTO Mobile Ad Network","location":"San Diego, CA, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><p><a href=\"http://motiveinteractive.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Motive Interactive\u00a0</a>was recently named one of the\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.hasoffers.com/blog/top-25-mobile-advertising-ecosystem/\" target=\"_blank\">Top 25 Mobile Ad Networks in the word,</a>\u00a0come join a team with an amazing future. Motive is seeking creative, driven, and out of the box thinkers to join our growing team in San Diego, CA. If you have what it takes to be the CTO of one of the fastest growing companies in the Mobile Ad Space this is your chance.\u00a0</p><p>Motive has been recognized by numerous publications including Inc. Magazine as one of the fastest growing companies in the United States. Motive is at the forefront of Mobile App Marketing and a proven leader in user acquisition for apps and mobile / online games.</p><p>We are searching for an experienced technologist to join our\u00a0management team as CTO.\u00a0The ideal candidate should have a passion for web and mobile development. The role will require hands-on experience across the stack- from MYSQL query optimization to cross-browser responsive HTML/CSS, and mobile development. We are a small team looking to grow, the CTO must be willing to dig in.\u00a0</p><p><strong>Skills, Responsibilities and\u00a0Requirements:</strong></p><ul> <li>    <p>Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science or equivalent education and experience a plus.</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Demonstrated experience and proficiency planning, developing, and maintaining applications and front-end systems.</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Experience in LAMP Development</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>Experience with Mobile Development</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>Experience with MVC Framework (Codeigniter is a plus)</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Experience with RESTful API/services</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Experience with Adserver such as OpenX</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>In-depth knowledge of web and mobile technologies, relevant software packages, and experience with dynamic data-driven web sites.</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Proven work experience with HTML, XML, CSS, Javascript (Photoshop is a plus)</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Familiarity with data transport formats (e.g., XML, JSON)</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Familiarity with mobile application development languages (Objective-C, Java) and mobile development frameworks (Phonegap).</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Lead web development efforts, including mentoring and advising peers.</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Troubleshoot and resolve issues with client systems.</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Lead web development efforts, including mentoring and advising peers.</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Ability to work independently, as well as in a team environment.</p> </li></ul><p><strong>Perks:</strong></p><ul>    <li>    <p>Work in a fast-paced development environment where you will see the results of your work immediately</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Casual relaxed atmosphere with a results- driven mentality</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>\u200bCompetitive base salary</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>Health benefits: Medical/dental/vision benefits</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>401K</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Profit from working with a team on the cutting edge of the mobile marketing and advertising industry.\u00a0</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Quickly expand your skills as an online marketing professional and build a valuable network in one of the fastest growing segments of advertising.</p>   </li></ul> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqQT\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqQd\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqQd</a></p>\n","company":"Motive Interactive","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/4f0531ae-9265-11e6-9b6e-cd45403bef14"},{"id":"2e72ddae-9262-11e6-9bad-8c493a525ee8","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 23:01:46 UTC 2016","title":"Full Stack Developer","location":"San Diego, CA, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><h3><strong>About Motive Interactive:</strong></h3><p><a href=\"http://motiveinteractive.com/\">Motive Interactive\u00a0</a>was recently named #5 on the\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.tune.com/blog/top-25-advertising-partners-spring-2015-edition/\">Top 25 Mobile Ad Networks in the world</a><a href=\"http://www.hasoffers.com/blog/top-25-mobile-advertising-ecosystem/\">!</a>\u00a0Motive is seeking creative, driven, and out-of-the box thinkers to join our growing team in San Diego, CA.</p><p>Motive has been recognized by numerous publications including Inc. Magazine as one of the fastest growing companies in the United States. Motive is at the forefront of Mobile App Marketing and a proven leader in user acquisition.\u00a0</p><p>The Full Stack Developer will be responsible for the analysis, development, enhancement, and\u00a0deployment of on-line systems in addition to design and development of customer spec database\u00a0systems and Internet-facing promotional sites and applications.</p><p>The qualified Full Stack\u00a0Web Developer candidate will possess a strong background with JS/PHP/LAMP, with lead\u00a0capabilities over other developers in a team environment. The developer will have experience with\u00a0workflows with numerous hops/limited latency. AdTech is strongly preferred.</p><p><strong>Developer Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:</strong></p><ul>  <li>Maintenance and management (end-to-end) of current SaaS based Mobile Ad Solution that has\u00a0multiple hops requiring limited latency</li> <li>Maintenance and management of internal operational applications and processes</li>  <li>Application of systems development lifecycle, engineering best practices, and team development\u00a0and leadership</li></ul><p><strong>Web Developer Required Skills:</strong></p><ul>  <li>Javascript</li> <li>JQuery</li> <li>PHP</li>    <li>RESTful APIs</li>   <li>Linux Apache</li>   <li>MySQL/SQL</li>  <li>HTML5</li>  <li>CSS</li>    <li>Desktop OS (Windows/Mac)</li></ul><p><strong>Web Developer Preferred Skills:</strong></p><ul>   <li>AdTech strongly preferred</li>  <li>AJAX</li>   <li>noSQL</li>  <li>Bootstrap</li>  <li>Responsive Design</li>  <li>Git/GitHub/Bitbucket (source and version control)</li>  <li>JAVA</li>   <li>Python</li> <li>DNS management</li> <li>AWS (Amazon Web Services) administration and understanding (EC2, RDS, S3)</li>  <li>MVC frameworks (CakePHP, Ruby, Django)</li></ul><p><strong>PERKS</strong></p><ul>   <li>Company recognized for its amazing Culture! Ranked as one of San Diego&#39;s best places to work.\u00a0</li>    <li>Work in a fast-paced development environment where you will see the results of your work immediately\u00a0</li> <li>Casual relaxed atmosphere with a results- driven mentality</li> <li>Competitive base salary</li>    <li>Health benefits: Medical/dental/vision benefits</li>    <li>401K</li>   <li>Profit from working with a team on the cutting edge of the mobile marketing and advertising industry.\u00a0</li>    <li>Quickly expand your skills as an online marketing professional and build a valuable network in one of the fastest growing segments of advertising</li>  <li>Complimentary massage therapy</li>  <li>Awesome company events!</li></ul><h3>\u00a0</h3><h3>\u00a0</h3> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqKz\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqLJ\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FqLJ</a></p>\n","company":"Motive Interactive","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/2e72ddae-9262-11e6-9bad-8c493a525ee8"},{"id":"47ede8ec-9207-11e6-9251-d3da2c53a0aa","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 12:12:22 UTC 2016","title":"Front-end developer","location":"Delft","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>One does not simply design a great UI!</p>\n\n<p>Do you believe Wordpress templates are an insult to your foo? Like to work with in-house born and bred APIs, that are still growing every day? Want to design an extraordinary top-of-stack UI for demanding users? Then read on, because this might just be the job you\u2019re looking for!</p>\n\n<p>At Nerdalize we are re-imagining cloud computing. We are not only the most sustainable, cost-effective and transparent cloud provider. We want to offer our users a professional cloud environment that is easy to use, will help do their jobs faster, and will work on all major OS platforms. This is where you come in.</p>\n\n<p>You will get full responsibility in developing our user interface from the very start. To make this happen, you will use your eye for detail without losing focus of the bigger picture. You base your decisions on continuous experiments and testing together with our users, working side by side with back-end developers, customer experience experts, and sales gurus. In the end it is all about developing a fully working cloud platform that makes our users happy, and you and us proud.</p>\n\n<p>Already feel a light (#ECECEC) fluttering inside while reading this? Find out below if we fit your bill!</p>\n\n<p><strong>You are the frond-end god / goddess who</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Understands core front-end web technologies (JavaScript, HTML, CSS) like no other</li>\n<li>Uses frameworks (like React, Ember or similar) as a second nature</li>\n<li>Passionately developed web-based interfaces on a project basis before</li>\n<li>Believes that the quality of an interface is only as good as its user feedback</li>\n<li>Is curious,flexible and eager to learn: every day can bring new customers, requirements, and API versions.</li>\n<li>Has experience with modern software development practices: e.g Agile/Scrum, (git) version control, automated testing and CI/CD.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>We offer you</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Impact and responsibility from day 0. You are designing and developing one of the most important parts of our product.</li>\n<li>A high performance team where cutting edge technology is the name of the game. If you know of something even newer and better, we love to hear it!</li>\n<li>Weekly demo time to show the whole team what crazy stuff you\u2019re working on. In return you get a cold beer and meaningful feedback.</li>\n<li>Champagne, to celebrate success together, and a pep talk to help you learn from your mistakes.</li>\n<li>Fun teammates for weird lunch discussions, team days, drinks, parties, and more.</li>\n<li>A workplace at Europe\u2019s biggest high-tech incubator: YES!Delft. The place is buzzing with young, vibrant people with a passion for Friday drinks, foosball, and working on great ideas to change the world (think: buildings on water, rockets, bird repelling lasers etc. etc.).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>In our team</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>We trust our colleagues and customers and actively seek to understand them.</li>\n<li>We are honest with each other and ourselves.</li>\n<li>We are self-starters who thrive with autonomy, and perceive \u201cchaos\u201d as an opportunity to shine.</li>\n<li>We love a good discussion and survive disagreements.</li>\n<li>We are willing and eager to learn from each other.</li>\n<li>We are transparent thinkers and action oriented doers.</li>\n<li>We are passionate about what we work on and take pride in what we develop.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Sounds to cool to be true? Come see for yourself! Get in touch and we\u2019ll show you around (coffee/tea/beer/wine provided).</p>\n\n<p><strong>Interested?</strong>\nApply via the <strong>&#39;Apply&#39;</strong> button.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Agency calls are not appreciated.</strong></p>\n\n<p><em>Keywords: front-end; full stack; UI; UX; design; frameworks; JavaScript; APIs</em></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://nerdalizecom.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/front_end_developer_delft/115293/V819/apply\">Click here to apply online!</a></p>\n","company":"Nerdalize","company_url":"https://nerdalizecom.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/f/115293/V819/apply","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/17f63784-9207-11e6-9279-acaf5d307d5e.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/47ede8ec-9207-11e6-9251-d3da2c53a0aa"},{"id":"6c13c802-9204-11e6-8d1b-6883d57a4814","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 11:51:14 UTC 2016","title":"Front-End Developer","location":"Amsterdam ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Jij wordt enthousiast van het bouwen van moderne gebruiksvriendelijke applicaties. Je wilt graag voorop lopen als het gaat om het uitdenken en realiseren van innovatieve oplossingen. Je vraagt veel van anderen maar het meeste van jezelf. Logisch, want je weet waarvoor je het doet. Je gelooft in vooruitgang.</p>\n\n<p>Front-End Developer\nFulltime, Amsterdam/Den Bosch</p>\n\n<p>Wat ga je doen\nJij bent verantwoordelijk voor het ontwikkelen, ontwerpen &amp; programmeren van online of mobile applicaties op basis van een visual en interactie ontwerp. Je zorgt voor de afstemming van de technische ontwerpen met alle collega\u2019s die eveneens bij het project betrokken zijn en voor een goede integratie. Je wilt graag voorop lopen als het gaat om het uitdenken en realiseren van een nieuwe verbeterde user experience. Je krijgt energie van het optimaliseren van de digitale klantbeleving. In het projectteam communiceer je over de voortgang van de werkzaamheden en vraagt tijdig om hulp indien deadlines in gevaar komen. Kortom, programmeren is jouw ding!</p>\n\n<p>Wat neem je mee\nEen gezonde dosis lef, pioniersmentaliteit, teamspirit (je kunt het tenslotte niet alleen) en jouw deskundigheid waar we versteld van staan!</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Het ontwikkelen in HTML5, CSS3, Javascript met frameworks als AngularJS en Bootstrap en het gebruik van RESTful API\u2019s klinkt je als muziek in de oren;</li>\n<li>Een Agile-Scrum-DevOps werkwijze is je op het lijf geschreven;</li>\n<li>Een grote pr\u00e9 is ervaring met een CMS als Sitecore;</li>\n<li>Je kan niet wachten om te bouwen aan de digitale toekomst van de bank.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Wat bieden we jou</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Een omgeving waarin je in samenwerking met UX designers innovatieve front-end applicaties ontwikkelt;</li>\n<li>Waarin je werkt met de nieuwste web development frameworks en technieken;</li>\n<li>Een nieuw team met collega\u2019s die allemaal beschikken over dezelfde drive en creativiteit;</li>\n<li>Flexibele werkplekken, korte lijnen en grote mate van autonomie;</li>\n<li>We vinden het belangrijk dat je je blijft ontwikkelen, daarom bieden wij verschillende trainings- en opleidingsmogelijkheden;</li>\n<li>Een eigenwijze omgeving met lef en durf waar je het verschil kan maken!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Waar geloven wij in\nAls innovatief en vernieuwend team binnen Van Lanschot staan wij ervoor dat onze klant altijd en overal zijn financi\u00eble informatie moet kunnen raadplegen. Onze klanten kiezen zelf op welke wijze ze contact met ons hebben. Natuurlijk kan dit persoonlijk via face-to-face contact. Maar wij als innovators binnen een traditionele bank geloven in de kracht van het nieuwe combineren met de mogelijkheden van het bestaande. Om op die manier onze klanten de beste dienstverlening te kunnen geven.</p>\n\n<p>Let\u2019s talk!\nZin om deze uitdaging als Front-end developer met ons aan te gaan? Bel/sms/app: Bas Rapati, Manager Digital Banking, 06 450 728 10 of solliciteer online via de link.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/front_end_developer_amsterdam/115305/V819/solliciteren\">Klik hier voor het sollicitatieformulier</a></p>\n\n<p>Web: <a href=\"http://www.werkenbijvanlanschot.nl/digital\">http://www.werkenbijvanlanschot.nl/digital</a>\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:talent@vanlanschot.com\">talent@vanlanschot.com</a> \nFacebook: @werkenbijvanlanschot\nLinkedIn: Van Lanschot Bankiers \nSkype: brapati</p>\n\n<p>Acquisitie naar aanleiding van deze vacature wordt niet op prijs gesteld. </p>\n\n<p>Trefwoorden: Vacature, Fulltime, Amsterdam, Software developer, Applicatie ontwikkelaar</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/f/115305/V819/solliciteren\">https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/f/115305/V819/solliciteren</a></p>\n","company":"Van Lanschot Bankiers","company_url":"https://corporate.vanlanschot.nl/werken","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/5bf5d988-9204-11e6-88af-d863cafc2d40.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/6c13c802-9204-11e6-8d1b-6883d57a4814"},{"id":"3e4c5a1c-9202-11e6-895b-80c9a43ce779","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 11:36:17 UTC 2016","title":"UI Engineer","location":"Palo Alto","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>UI Engineer</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Job description</strong><br />\nYou&rsquo;re a product-obsessed UI engineer who evaluates all of your work through the lens of user experience. You&rsquo;ve created a number of fully-formed software products that have been released into the wild and maintained. You have an eye for detail and a love for crafting highly-polished user interfaces with delightful micro-interactions. Your design skills are well-rounded, with experience working at all levels of design - product, interaction, and visual. You know what makes great typography and how it should be applied.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBecause the range of projects is diverse, we need a UI&nbsp;engineer with experience working on a wide variety of projects &ndash; building custom UI components, implementing responsive interfaces or working to improve the responsiveness and performance of our application. You&rsquo;ll work directly with designers to create new customer-facing features, from idea, through prototype, to release and maintenance.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\n<strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>People are the most important part of Delighted, and we take care of our own</li>\n    <li>Work remotely or from our beautiful downtown Palo Alto office</li>\n    <li>Top-tier health insurance with maximized benefits and coverage</li>\n    <li>Unlimited equipment budget</li>\n    <li>Relocation assistance</li>\n    <li>Flexible schedule</li>\n    <li>Generous maternity and paternity leave</li>\n    <li>Unlimited vacation and paid time off&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>About the team</strong><br />\nWe are a small design-driven team, focused on impeccable user experience. Simplicity, quality and care inform our decisions and processes. We believe in a collaborative, feedback-rich design process and feel that great experiences can only come from teams who care deeply. This is the company we&rsquo;ve always wanted to exist. We share what this all means to us on our blog.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>Our front-end is built with CoffeeScript, SASS and HAML. As such, you should have a deep understanding of <strong>HTML</strong>, <strong>CSS</strong> and <strong>JavaScript</strong>. You should also have experience working with front-end JavaScript frameworks, especially <strong>React.js</strong>. You should know how to structure maintainable CSS for large projects.</li>\n    <li>HTTP is the conduit between our front-end and back-end, and as a UI engineer you should have a thorough understanding of this layer of the stack. This includes deep knowledge of cookies, caching, AJAX, cross-domain sharing, security issues, etc.</li>\n    <li>Our back-end runs on Rails with MySQL, Redis, and Elasticsearch on AWS. You should have experience building interfaces for complex applications that are powered by <strong>Rails</strong>.</li>\n    <li>We write automated tests for all of our code. You should be passionate about testing since you know it&rsquo;s the only way to deliver high quality software.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Interested?&nbsp;</strong><br />\nSubmit your application with resume and personal information via our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ltpx.nl/SNUA7gp\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>online application form</strong></a>.<br />\n<br />\nVisit our website at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ltpx.nl/N7QTMpz\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>delighted.com</strong></a>&nbsp;for more information.<br />\n<br />\n<em>Acquisition is not appreciated regarding this vacancy.</em><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://bcontrol.brockmeyer.nl/track.php?orderid=20297\" style=\"height:0;width:0\" /></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://ltpx.nl/OwNbHli\" target=\"_self\">Click here to apply</a></p>\n","company":"Delighted","company_url":"http://www.delighted.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/2d8a67fa-9202-11e6-999e-05ce54507da8.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/3e4c5a1c-9202-11e6-895b-80c9a43ce779"},{"id":"e32e2080-9200-11e6-98fa-aeebc86732c9","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 11:26:59 UTC 2016","title":"Cloud Operations Engineer","location":"Wroclaw, Poland","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>About us</strong></p>\n\n<p>We are Unit4, a leading provider of enterprise applications empowering people in service organizations. We are on a mission, because we no longer accept the digital downgrade that people experience when they swap their personal devices for their work ones. We create business software that works the way people want, not the other way around.</p>\n\n<p>Saas Operations will use Devops methology to work with both cross functional scrum teams as well as customer facing support groups. A Saas Engineer supports the deployment, and operations of Unit4 Global scale products. The Saas engineer collaborates with his/her teammates to monitor, handle incidents, configuration management and to improve solutions in Unit4 cloud platform. In this role, the engineer will work to deploy and operate our Cloud Service, help automate and streamline our operations and processes, and build and maintain tools for deployment, monitoring and operations. The engineer will troubleshoot and resolve issues in our customer facing production environments.</p>\n\n<p><strong>What you will do</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You will be responsible for deployment and release of customer software on Unit4 cloud platform</li>\n<li>You will be in charge of automating of software deployment with support od scripting tools (ie.PowerShell and JSON)</li>\n<li>You will be responsible for configuration management and infrastructure provisioning, performance and security monitoring of customer software and infrastructure</li>\n<li>You will cooperate with Product Owner in definition of operational requirements and with development team in creation and deployment of secure, stable and reliable solutions</li>\n<li>You will work in close interaction with Customer Support team in customer issues analysis, prioritisation and resolution</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Your approach</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Eager to learn new technologies</li>\n<li>Communicative and helpful across domain teams</li>\n<li>Ability to focus on solutions instead of problems</li>\n<li>Analytical and structured</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>We ask</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 3 years higher education within information technology and/or equivalent relevant experience within software development.</li>\n<li>Experience in deployment of applications and IT operation</li>\n<li>Experience on automation and scripting tools (PowerShell, JSON or other script languages).</li>\n<li>Experience with network infrastructure and security aspects</li>\n<li>Experience of Hyper-V and VM technologies</li>\n<li>Experience or knowledge of MS SQL and performance tuning</li>\n<li>Knowledge of MFT and Webservices</li>\n<li>Knowledge of different Azure technologies</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Configuration Management</li>\n<li>Knowledge of development processes, SCRUM etc.</li>\n<li>Fluent in written and spoken English</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>We offer</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work with cutting edge technology</li>\n<li>Stable employment with an attractive salary</li>\n<li>Various benefits such as: private medical care, Multisport, pre-paid lunch cards and many others</li>\n<li>Sport and integration events</li>\n<li>International work experience</li>\n<li>Opportunity fo meeting people from various countries and cultures</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Applying in English \u2013 why?</strong></p>\n\n<p>Unit4 is an international software company with business units all over the world. We cherish our cultural differences and celebrate our common values. English is the common language in our company and therefore we kindly ask you to submit your cv and cover letter in English.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Please apply through our Global Career Website: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/2doUl4u\">http://bit.ly/2doUl4u</a></p>\n","company":"Unit4","company_url":"http://www.unit4.com","company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/e32e2080-9200-11e6-98fa-aeebc86732c9"},{"id":"77c61b3a-91f7-11e6-923a-bbef9c460c4f","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 10:18:34 UTC 2016","title":"1 x Node.js Engineer / 1 x Android Lead / 1 x UX/UI Lead","location":"London","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>Leading UK healthcare technology startup looking to fill 3 different positions</strong></p>\n\n<p>Echo is an advanced platform to order and manage prescription medications and our patent-pending system tells users when to take their medication and when they are about to run out. The market size is huge and just in the UK, it is a 1.25bn+ medication item / \u00a310bn+ revenue opportunity. Using our disruptive technology we firmly believe that we solve a number of customer pain-points and make the system as a whole significantly more efficient.</p>\n\n<p>Echo is growing quickly, so we are looking for some passionate, motivated and ambitious individuals to join us. You need to love user experience, strive for robust and scalable solutions and be willing to roll your sleeves up and work beyond the remit of your role. We are super excited to get our product out to customers and if you like what you see, do get in touch.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Role 1. NODE.JS RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implementation, testing and integration of services</li>\n<li>Steer technical direction of projects</li>\n<li>Take complete ownership of project work-streams</li>\n<li>Lead both architecture and development efforts across projects</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Role 2. ANDROID RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop Android native app and it\u2019s integration with core services</li>\n<li>Work with a team of developers and UI/UX to write best code and exceptional user interface </li>\n<li>Develop and manage automated unit tests</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Role 3. UX &amp; UI RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Take full ownership of UI/UX across all platforms, working between product and technology teams</li>\n<li>Be Echo\u2019s design champion, putting the user first and designing cool, easy to use products people love </li>\n<li>Bridge the gap between product vision and technological reality; create designs that are ambitious but practical, emphasising iterative design</li>\n<li>Build and inspire a team of designers making Echo Europe\u2019s destination employer for design talent</li>\n<li>Test and learn, using both qualitative and quantitative methods to optimise user experience</li>\n<li>As part of Echo\u2019s leadership, be responsible for shaping future product roadmap across wearables and new markets</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>TECH STACK</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Back End: JavaScript ES6, Node.js, Firebase</li>\n<li>Front End: TypeScript, Angular 2, SCSS, HTML5, Firebase, Material Design, Webpack </li>\n<li>Mobile: Swift, Firebase, Java</li>\n<li>Data: RapidMiner</li>\n<li>APIs: Mandrill, Stripe, EasyPost</li>\n<li>Operations: GitHub, Travis CI, Google Cloud Platform</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>DESIRED SKILLS &amp; EXPERIENCE</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Proficiency in one of the programming languages from our stack</li>\n<li>Significant experience working with some (ideally most) of the technologies from our stack </li>\n<li>Solid experience developing mobile and / or web applications</li>\n<li>Experience with API design, development and integration</li>\n<li>Experience with continuous integration and cloud computing services</li>\n<li>Experience leading development teams</li>\n<li>Proven UI experience in making complex user-journeys simple (UX/UI only)</li>\n<li>Proven UX experience, with an eye for detail (UX/UI only)</li>\n<li>Solid experience developing mobile/web applications at a top-tier startup, agency or company (UX/UI only)</li>\n<li>Experience leading product and/or design teams  (UX/UI only)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>BONUS SKILLS &amp; EXPERIENCE</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with large data sets</li>\n<li>Experience working on R&amp;D projects</li>\n<li>Exposure to some of the following technologies: Electron, Ionic, Meteor, Polymer, React, RxJS</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>BENEFITS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Highly competitive package</li>\n<li>25 days of annual holiday + 3 days extra between Xmas and New Year 1 flexible work from home day</li>\n<li>Apple equipment</li>\n<li>Fruit basket Mondays</li>\n<li>Craft beer &amp; learn o\u2019clock Fridays</li>\n<li>Team lunch &amp; drinks once a month</li>\n<li>Ticket to a local tech event once a month</li>\n<li>Fresh single origin coffee &amp; artisan loose leaf teas</li>\n<li>Definitely no instant coffee \uf609</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Email CV/resume to <a href=\"mailto:careers@echo.co.uk\">careers@echo.co.uk</a></p>\n","company":"Echo (backed by 3 lead VCs)","company_url":"http://www.echo.co.uk","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/f06067ae-918d-11e6-93c1-b7301dabcef9.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/77c61b3a-91f7-11e6-923a-bbef9c460c4f"},{"id":"2de13c80-91a6-11e6-8d9d-796b882c1bac","created_at":"Fri Oct 14 00:36:19 UTC 2016","title":"Software Engineer","location":"Palo Alto, CA (or remote)","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>You\u2019re a product-obsessed software engineer who evaluates all of your work through the lens of user experience, regardless of which layer of the stack you\u2019re working in. You\u2019ve created a number of fully-formed software products that have been released into the wild. You believe that code is a means to an end, not the end itself.</p>\n\n<p>Because the range of projects is diverse, we need a full-stack Rails engineer with experience working on a wide variety of products. You\u2019ll work on projects like: improving our natural language date range search, implementing integrations with 3rd party services, or working to improve the responsiveness and reliability of our API. You\u2019ll also work with the entire team in creating new customer-facing features, from idea, through prototype, to release and maintenance.</p>\n\n<h2>Technical background</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Our backend runs on Rails with MySQL, Redis, and Elasticsearch on AWS. You should have experience building scalable and maintainable services with Rails.</p></li>\n<li><p>Our front-end is built with CoffeeScript, SASS and HAML. You should have a deep understanding of HTML, CSS and Javascript.</p></li>\n<li><p>The glue between our front-end and back-end is HTTP, so you should have a thorough understanding of this part of the stack including: cookies, caching, AJAX, cross-domain sharing, security issues, etc.</p></li>\n<li><p>We write automated tests for all of our code. You should be passionate about testing since you know it\u2019s the only way to deliver high quality software.</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Benefits</h2>\n\n<p>People are the most important part of Delighted, and we take care of our own.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work remotely or from our beautiful downtown Palo Alto office</li>\n<li>Top-tier health insurance with maximized benefits and coverage</li>\n<li>Unlimited equipment budget</li>\n<li>Relocation assistance</li>\n<li>Flexible schedule</li>\n<li>Generous maternity and paternity leave</li>\n<li>Unlimited vacation and paid time off</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>About the team</h2>\n\n<p>We are a small design-driven team, focused on impeccable user experience. Simplicity, quality, and care inform our decisions and processes. We believe in a collaborative, feedback-rich design process, and feel that great experiences can only come from teams who care deeply. This is the company we\u2019ve always wanted to exist.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>If you\u2019re interested, please send a link to your Github account and any products you\u2019ve worked on recently of which you are particularly proud to jobs@delighted.com. We prefer great work over resumes.</p>\n","company":"Delighted","company_url":"https://delighted.com/jobs/software-engineer","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/183b9aba-91a6-11e6-8516-13cdd84cd6da.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/2de13c80-91a6-11e6-8d9d-796b882c1bac"},{"id":"fad20200-9198-11e6-9503-bb3a41d40c7a","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 23:01:31 UTC 2016","title":"Technical Support","location":"North America (Remote)","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>The GitHub Technical Support team is looking for full-time team members in located in North America (US and Canada)! This person will join GitHub as part of our global support team and support our customers around the world.</p>\n\n<p>GitHub users work 24/7, so you&#39;ll occasionally need to adjust your work week to help cover a weekend or holiday (don&#39;t worry! We strongly support flexible schedules that let you to take care of the important things in your life).</p>\n\n<p>When GitHub users have questions, they contact Support and we help them as quickly and awesomely as possible. Technical support handles a wide variety of inquiries including questions about Git and GitHub workflows, GitHub Pages, our API, and our desktop applications. Support also works closely with the engineering team to track down bugs and improve our documentation.</p>\n\n<p>The most important characteristic of our support team is that we love helping developers. GitHub is a place for people to work better, together. Our job is to help. Support treats users the way we&#39;d want someone to treat our friends.</p>\n\n<p>Our support teammates have excellent writing chops: stellar grammar, charming written personality, and the ability to explain complicated things simply. We measure our success in swiftness, accuracy, and clarity.</p>\n\n<h2>WHAT YOU SHOULD HAVE:</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Currently resides and has legal working authorization for Canada or the US</li>\n<li>Experience using GitHub</li>\n<li>Exposure to programming with a language like Ruby</li>\n<li>Basic experience using Git</li>\n<li>Understanding of how websites and web applications work</li>\n<li>Stellar English and grammar skills</li>\n<li>Excellent problem solving skills \u2013 you might not know all the answers but you know how to find and communicate the solution</li>\n<li>A strong sense of empathy \u2013 you are attuned to hear the question behind a question</li>\n<li>Customer service experience</li>\n<li>A unique writing style and voice</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>BONUS POINTS FOR:</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Will love developers and GitHub as much as we do</li>\n<li>Could effortlessly explain how Git works to a non-developer</li>\n<li>Have remote customer service experience</li>\n<li>Experience working from the command line</li>\n<li>Familiar with basic network concepts and tools</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>About GitHub</p>\n\n<p>WHO WE ARE</p>\n\n<p>GitHub is the best place to share code with friends, co-workers, classmates, and complete strangers. Over ten million people use GitHub to build amazing things together. With the collaborative features of GitHub.com, our desktop and mobile apps, and GitHub Enterprise, it has never been easier for individuals and teams to write better code, faster.</p>\n\n<p>We have a lot of exciting things to do, and we\u2019re looking for the right people to grow with us!</p>\n\n<p>WHY YOU SHOULD JOIN</p>\n\n<p>Working at GitHub is, to put it simply, a special slice of the universe. We&#39;re committed to transparency, collaboration, experimentation, and always staying classy.</p>\n\n<p>Because of this unique perspective, we&#39;ve established one of the most flexible and well designed physical workspaces around that encourages you to work as you work best. Right now, over 60% of our employees are based outside of our San Francisco (SOMA) headquarters and work according to how they get their best stuff done.</p>\n\n<p>Ensuring that GitHubbers are healthy, motivated, focused and creative is how GitHub stays awesome. Part of this is ensuring that our benefits* are out of this world.</p>\n\n<p>In a nutshell, we&#39;ve built and are growing a place where we truly love working, and we think you will too.</p>\n\n<p>GitHub is made up of people with many different backgrounds and lifestyles, and we like it that way. We invite applications from people of all stripes. We don&#39;t discriminate against employees or applicants based on gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, race, religion, age, national origin, citizenship, pregnancy status, veteran status, or any other differences that people imagine to discriminate against one another. Also, if you have a disability, please let us know if there&#39;s anything we can do to make the interview process better for you; we&#39;re happy to accommodate.</p>\n\n<p>*Please note that benefits vary by country, if you have any questions don&#39;t hesitate to ask your recruiter!</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Interested? We would love to hear more about you and your interest in joining us at GitHub! Just fill out our application <a href=\"https://jobs.lever.co/github/82eca75e-6d84-469d-8f1c-bdf89c9e106c\">here</a>!</p>\n","company":"GitHub","company_url":"https://github.com/about/jobs","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/f876313e-9198-11e6-8614-08ce9ed3a8dd.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/fad20200-9198-11e6-9503-bb3a41d40c7a"},{"id":"584a4248-9181-11e6-9c2a-a054ba8f57ca","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 20:13:20 UTC 2016","title":"Principal Software Engineer","location":"Boston, Massachusetts","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Harvard University</p>\n\n<p>School/Unit\nHarvard Medical School</p>\n\n<h2>Sub-Unit</h2>\n\n<p>Job Function\nInformation Technology</p>\n\n<p>Time Status\nFull-time</p>\n\n<p>Department\nHMS Online Programs - External Education</p>\n\n<p>Salary Grade\n059</p>\n\n<p>Union\n00 - Non Union, Exempt or Temporary</p>\n\n<p>Duties &amp; Responsibilities\nAs a member of the HMX team in the Office for Online Learning, the Principal Software Engineer will have an opportunity to make a difference in shaping an innovative educational experience. This role oversees the technical aspects of the delivery of HMX&#39;s innovative, high-quality online educational modules.</p>\n\n<p>The Principal Software Engineer is responsible for the development and delivery of the HMX online learning experience, overseeing all aspects of HMX&#39;s Open edX online education platform to ensure that the project plan, schedules, feature set and quality standards are met. Reporting to the Faculty Director of HMX, the Principal Software Engineer will write platform code and work closely with the curriculum development and media leads and with external technology vendors.</p>\n\n<p>As a member of a small team in a fast-paced, entrepreneurial environment, the ideal candidate should feel comfortable both coding and working closely with tech-savvy, forward-thinking colleagues to conceptualize, find, develop, and deliver optimal technology solutions to support learning. Curiosity, creativity, and initiative are a must, along with a desire to develop superior educational products and services that effectively contribute to online learning and engagement.</p>\n\n<p>Applicants should include links to their code at GitHub or another repository hosting service, as well as a cover letter describing why this position interests them and how it fits their experience and interests.</p>\n\n<p>As Principal Software Engineer, you will be responsible for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Leading all aspects of development on an Open edX based learning platform</li>\n<li>Contributing as a hands-on developer, including leading the writing of software in support of all platform components</li>\n<li>Serving as the main point of contact for external contractors</li>\n<li>Working with HMS Online Learning leadership to define product features and roadmap for courses</li>\n<li>Working closely with the content/pedagogy and media teams to enable creation and delivery of world-class course content, as well as back-end workflow</li>\n<li>Developing and/or integrating services that integrate with the HMX platform, for example, an ecommerce solution that encompasses registration and enrollment processes</li>\n<li>Maintaining HMX platform configuration, security, data backup, code and documentation in an effective and timely fashion</li>\n<li>Installing, configuring and maintaining systems/stacks in support of HMX development projects, primarily on AWS</li>\n<li>Working across the project team to identify options and opportunities for leveraging of third party applications and services, when required</li>\n<li>Researching and proposing product solutions that maximize the use of team resources by leveraging open-source contributions to Open edX </li>\n<li>Collaborating with the operations, content, and media teams to respond to user feedback and prioritize new feature requests</li>\n<li>Developing new interactive educational tools, for example for Xblocks implementing innovative assessment types for the Open edX platform, including managing the associated technology and platform requirements</li>\n<li>Managing creation of the front-end interface from provided design concepts, using HTML5 and JavaScript frameworks and libraries, and ensuring that the platform functions well on mobile devices</li>\n<li>Designing and building or adapting technology workflows and solutions for collecting data from the online platform and performing data analysis</li>\n<li>Overseeing design and development of dashboard/visualizations for learning analytics</li>\n<li>Participating in and contributing to HMX internal team meetings and projects as well as activities focused on integration of research and pedagogical innovation</li>\n<li>Overseeing a small internal team as well as contractors</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Basic Qualifications\n8 years of technology-based work experience; or BS in Computer Science/related field with at least 5 years of technology-based work experience. Hands on experience with front end and back end development.</p>\n\n<p>Additional Qualifications\nPrevious experience in web software development and more specifically with the Open edX platform in all aspects. Expertise in Python, along with strong knowledge of HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, and modern UI frameworks is expected.</p>\n\n<p>The ideal candidate would possess most or all of the following:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience in development of platform/tools for online learning, particularly Open edX</li>\n<li>5+ years of experience designing, developing, and implementing web applications, including experience developing e-learning applications</li>\n<li>Previous experience as technical lead in an engineering team</li>\n<li>Full life cycle development experience (technical design through implementation) and experience with agile development practices</li>\n<li>Experience in vendor and third party management, including managing relationships over extended periods of time</li>\n<li>Strong knowledge of both server side and presentation layer development technologies, including prior programming experience in with one or more language(s), e.g. JavaScript and/or Python</li>\n<li>Enthusiasm, sense of humor, and a love of creative product design for extending the possibilities for online learning </li>\n<li>Strong leadership, interpersonal, and written/verbal communication skills</li>\n<li>Expertise in the following technologies / frameworks: Django/Python; web front end / client side languages (HTML, CSS, JavaScript / jQuery, AJAX, JSON); NoSQL (e.g. MongoDB) and traditional SQL database systems (e.g. MySQL); experience with visualization libraries (e.g. D3.js, Raphael, Processing.js) is a plus. Knowledge of AWS is beneficial.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Pre-Employment Screening\nEducation\nIdentity</p>\n\n<p>EEO Statement\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. </p>\n\n<p>Apply Here: <a href=\"https://jobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?sec=1&amp;partnerid=25240&amp;siteid=5341&amp;jobId=1236799&amp;type=search&amp;JobReqLang=1&amp;recordstart=1\">https://jobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?sec=1&amp;partnerid=25240&amp;siteid=5341&amp;jobId=1236799&amp;type=search&amp;JobReqLang=1&amp;recordstart=1</a></p>\n\n<p>PI95627922</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Apply Online: <a href=\"https://jobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?sec=1&amp;partnerid=25240&amp;siteid=5341&amp;jobId=1236799&amp;type=search&amp;JobReqLang=1&amp;recordstart=1\">https://jobs.brassring.com/TGWEbHost/jobdetails.aspx?sec=1&amp;partnerid=25240&amp;siteid=5341&amp;jobId=1236799&amp;type=search&amp;JobReqLang=1&amp;recordstart=1</a></p>\n","company":"Harvard Medical School","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/584a4248-9181-11e6-9c2a-a054ba8f57ca"},{"id":"7d219d52-917f-11e6-9c29-71aa2d4a94c6","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 19:59:02 UTC 2016","title":"Support Tools Application Engineer","location":"United States ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Are you a self starter who loves autonomy and helping others in the workplace? Passionate about crafting internal tools and helping our Support Team scale? We have the role for you. </p>\n\n<p>It takes great tools to give great support to GitHub&#39;s ten million users and that is why GitHub is looking for a Support Tools Application Engineer to join a team of compassionate people building and maintaining those internal support tools.</p>\n\n<p>From our custom-built ticketing system and our Jekyll-powered Help site to our documentation deployment toolchainand third-party integrations, you\u2019ll be responsible for the technology that keeps our support teams working efficiently.</p>\n\n<p><strong>About Support Tools</strong></p>\n\n<p>We are a small distributed team who works on tooling for GitHub&#39;s Support teams. Our software helps Support with customer support issues, documentation publishing, customer account management, and support business analysis. You will have an opportunity to work on various projects that are typically built in Ruby, on Rails, or using NPM for front-end work and build tools.</p>\n\n<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>You will write, test, and review application code</p></li>\n<li><p>You will influence and inform the technical direction of internal projects</p></li>\n<li><p>You will detect and respond to changes in application health</p></li>\n<li><p>You will collect and analyze Support metrics to drive improvements</p></li>\n<li><p>You will document the systems you build</p></li>\n<li><p>You will encourage and assist the technical growth of your peers</p></li>\n<li><p>You will work with the Support teams to define and prioritize projects</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>ABOUT YOU:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>You have at least 3 years of software development experience</p></li>\n<li><p>You have worked on an active production Ruby web application</p></li>\n<li><p>You are comfortable writing modern JavaScript</p></li>\n<li><p>You have solid SQL and general database knowledge</p></li>\n<li><p>You have a solid knowledge of testing principles</p></li>\n<li><p>You are familiar with metrics-driven application monitoring</p></li>\n<li><p>You have excellent communication skills, especially when working with a distributed team</p></li>\n<li><p>You have strong empathy for GitHub users and GitHub Support</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>BONUS POINTS FOR EXPERIENCE WITH:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Technical support for a web application</p></li>\n<li><p>ElasticSearch</p></li>\n<li><p>AWS or similar cloud computing operations</p></li>\n<li><p>Jekyll, Nanoc, or other static site generators</p></li>\n<li><p>Darwin Information Typing Architecture (DITA) authoring and publishing</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>GitHub is committed to building a diverse workforce and strongly encourages applications from people of color and other groups currently underrepresented in tech. We are looking for candidates who:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Display a strong commitment to building an inclusive tech environment</p></li>\n<li><p>Have demonstrated resilience and resourcefulness both in and outside of the workplace</p></li>\n<li><p>Can bring a new perspective based on unique educational, professional, and lived experiences</p></li>\n<li><p>Can effectively communicate with people from disparate backgrounds</p></li>\n<li><p>Have experience mentoring/coaching/teaching, particularly in environments with diverse students/participants</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>WHO WE ARE</strong></p>\n\n<p>GitHub is the best place to share code with friends, co-workers, classmates, and complete strangers. Over ten million people use GitHub to build amazing things together. With the collaborative features of GitHub.com, our desktop and mobile apps, and GitHub Enterprise, it has never been easier for individuals and teams to write better code, faster.</p>\n\n<p>We have a lot of exciting things to do, and we\u2019re looking for the right people to grow with us!</p>\n\n<p><strong>WHY YOU SHOULD JOIN</strong></p>\n\n<p>Working at GitHub is, to put it simply, a special slice of the universe. We&#39;re committed to transparency, collaboration, experimentation, and always staying classy.</p>\n\n<p>Because of this unique perspective, we&#39;ve established one of the most flexible and well designed physical workspaces around that encourages you to work as you work best. Right now, over 60% of our employees are based outside of our San Francisco (SOMA) headquarters and work according to how they get their best stuff done.</p>\n\n<p>Ensuring that GitHubbers are healthy, motivated, focused and creative is how GitHub stays awesome. Part of this is ensuring that our benefits* are out of this world.</p>\n\n<p>In a nutshell, we&#39;ve built and are growing a place where we truly love working, and we think you will too.</p>\n\n<p>GitHub is made up of people with many different backgrounds and lifestyles, and we like it that way. We invite applications from people of all stripes. We don&#39;t discriminate against employees or applicants based on gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, race, religion, age, national origin, citizenship, disability, pregnancy status, veteran status, or any other differences that people imagine to discriminate against one another. Also, if you have a disability, please let us know if there&#39;s anything we can do to make the interview process better for you; we&#39;re happy to accommodate.</p>\n\n<p>*Please note that benefits vary by country, if you have any questions don&#39;t hesitate to ask your recruiter!</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Apply on our <a href=\"https://jobs.lever.co/github/e25ccb5e-7683-4efe-8145-0a9e20b0b9b6\">Careers Page</a>.</p>\n","company":"GitHub","company_url":"https://jobs.lever.co/github/e25ccb5e-7683-4efe-8145-0a9e20b0b9b6","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/7825e088-917f-11e6-8748-0baef57ad9c6.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/7d219d52-917f-11e6-9c29-71aa2d4a94c6"},{"id":"7bbfeffa-9151-11e6-8415-dc63871964c8","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 14:30:27 UTC 2016","title":"Software Architect","location":"Amsterdam ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Jij wordt enthousiast als we het hebben over technische architectuur. Je wilt graag voorop lopen als het gaat om het uitdenken en realiseren van software oplossingen en je krijgt energie van ingewikkelde software- ontwikkelingstrajecten. Je vraagt veel van anderen maar het meeste van jezelf. Logisch, want je weet waarvoor je het doet. Je gelooft in vooruitgang.</p>\n\n<p>Software Architect\nFulltime, Amsterdam/Den Bosch</p>\n\n<p>Wat ga je doen\nJij bent verantwoordelijk voor het in kaart brengen van het bestaande softwaresysteem en gaat daarnaast ook aan de slag met het ontwikkelen van software architectuur. Jij kunt een vertaalslag maken van concepten en idee\u00ebn naar concrete software oplossingen en bent het aanspreekpunt voor de software-ontwikkelingstrajecten die op de technische roadmap staan. Je zorgt ook voor adviezen richting opdrachtgevers en stakeholders omtrent de inrichting van de softwaresystemen en de bijbehorende technische keuzes. In het kort, jij bewaakt en onderhoudt de\ntechnische architectuur en beheert de technische roadmap.</p>\n\n<p>Wat neem je mee\nEen gezonde dosis lef, pioniersmentaliteit, teamspirit (je kunt het tenslotte niet alleen) en jouw deskundigheid waar we versteld van staan!</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Je hebt je sporen verdiend als ontwikkelaar in Web/Mobile projecten en omgevingen;</li>\n<li>Je hebt relevante werkervaring als (software) architect;</li>\n<li>Je beschikt over abstract denkvermogen en overzicht en je bent een communicatietalent;</li>\n<li>Je blijft op de hoogte van wat er op technisch gebied speelt, zonder dat je de business uit het oog verliest;</li>\n<li>Je kan niet wachten om te bouwen aan de digitale toekomst van de bank.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Wat bieden we jou</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Een uitdagende omgeving waarin je de architectuur van de te ontwikkelen software (Web/Mobile) definieert aan de hand van specificaties en de realisatie ervan begeleid;</li>\n<li>Je staat aan de basis van het opstellen en onderhouden van ontwikkelrichtlijnen en standaarden;</li>\n<li>Een nieuw team met collega\u2019s die allemaal beschikken over dezelfde drive en creativiteit;</li>\n<li>Flexibele werkplekken, korte lijnen en grote mate van autonomie;</li>\n<li>We vinden het belangrijk dat je je blijft ontwikkelen, daarom bieden wij verschillende trainings- en opleidingsmogelijkheden;</li>\n<li>Een eigenwijze omgeving met lef en durf waar je het verschil kan maken!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Waar geloven wij in\nAls innovatief en vernieuwend team binnen Van Lanschot staan wij ervoor dat onze klant altijd en overal zijn financi\u00eble informatie moet kunnen raadplegen. Onze klanten kiezen zelf op welke wijze ze contact met ons hebben. Natuurlijk kan dit persoonlijk via face-to-face contact. Maar wij als innovators binnen een traditionele bank geloven in de kracht van het nieuwe combineren met de mogelijkheden van het bestaande. Om op die manier onze klanten de beste dienstverlening te kunnen geven.</p>\n\n<p>Let\u2019s talk!\nZin om deze uitdaging als Software Architect met ons aan te gaan? Solliciteer online via de link.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/software_architect_amsterdam/115317/V819/solliciteren\">Klik hier voor het sollicitatieformulier!</a></p>\n\n<p>Bel/sms/app: Bas Rapati, Manager Digital Banking, 06 450 728 10\nWeb: <a href=\"http://www.werkenbijvanlanschot.nl/digital\">http://www.werkenbijvanlanschot.nl/digital</a>\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:talent@vanlanschot.com\">talent@vanlanschot.com</a> \nFacebook: @werkenbijvanlanschot \nLinkedIn: Van Lanschot Bankiers \nSkype: brapati</p>\n\n<p>Acquisitie naar aanleiding van deze vacature wordt niet op prijs gesteld.</p>\n\n<p>Trefwoorden: Vacature, Fulltime, Amsterdam, Software engineer, Software developer.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/s/115317/V819/solliciteren\">https://vanlanschot.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/s/115317/V819/solliciteren</a></p>\n","company":"Van Lanschot Bankiers","company_url":"https://corporate.vanlanschot.nl/werken","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/77d12f26-9151-11e6-931e-1e16a11656ab.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/7bbfeffa-9151-11e6-8415-dc63871964c8"},{"id":"d9e9f7b2-914f-11e6-8dfb-bf85356a54df","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 14:18:24 UTC 2016","title":"Chief Technology Officer","location":"New York","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>We&#39;re looking for an aboslutely top-of-the line CTO with at least 5 years of real-world experience in building and managing read-world Web applications used by a significant number of real users.</p>\n\n<p>We have a very strong foundation to build on: A great product, with minimal technical debt, wonderful customers who love to co-create the product with us, and who are doing important work in the world that we get the opportunity to support and serve. Also, we&#39;re bootstrapped, profitable and proud, and growing at a steady clip.</p>\n\n<p>As our new CTO, you&#39;ll be in charge of driving both the technical development of our services and the product itself forward. You&#39;ll be responsible for the entire product lifecycle, ranging from implementation through to operations, and you have experience doing so following modern best practises. Because we are a relatively small company, it is important that you yourself have experience with the entire range of responsibilities and can take charge in getting things done. Equally, we&#39;re a growing business, so it is a requirement that you have at least two years of managerial experience at either an executive or VP level, and you get a kick out of building a lean team that gets things done.</p>\n\n<p>In your daily activities, you will be working closely with both our CEO, Calvin, on the product development, as well as working with our customer team to manage providing technical support to as well a collaborate with our beloved customers.</p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re looking for someone who gets off on solving problems effectively, meaning you don&#39;t settle on the first and best understanding of what the problem is before you jump to solutions. You keep looking at the problem from all the different angles until a simple solution appears. You simplify the complex.</p>\n\n<p>You love to figure things out that you&#39;ve never had to figure out before. You love to grow personally and professionally. You like using your own judgment and figuring out what needs to be done, given the vision and the values. You &quot;get&quot; things easily.</p>\n\n<p>If this is you, we can\u2019t wait to hear from you!</p>\n\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>2+ of experience building and managing a lean and efficient team following modern best practises of the field, with a remote component being a definite plus</li>\n<li>5+ years of experience using a range of modern front and backend technologies, such as Ruby on Rails, Django, Node.js or similar, along with database technologies such as relational databases like MySQL and PostgreSQL and more modern data stores such as ElasticSearch, Redis and the likes.</li>\n<li>5+ years of experience running production web applications operations on cloud platforms such as AWS.</li>\n<li>Strong product management skills.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Email <a 