 you?</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Join a company with a strong culture and human code of conduct</li>\n<li>Be a part of the development of the next generation of Gandi&#39;s products</li>\n<li>Work with new technologies and agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Tackle challenges with highly skilled coworkers</li>\n<li>Good health insurance</li>\n<li>Meal tickets on a 60/40 basis</li>\n<li>Transportation on a 50/50 basis</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Please include your Skype or Hangouts id for the first interview and send your resume in English and/or project portfolio (GitHub, etc.), thank you!</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"mailto:jobs@gandi.net\">jobs@gandi.net</a></p>\n","company":"Gandi.net","company_url":"https://www.gandi.net","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/6199d054-9148-11e6-9334-b1ab327b4134.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/74def2f2-9148-11e6-9278-581813ec12af"},{"id":"0cd2f3aa-9127-11e6-80a7-ba0fc907dd8a","created_at":"Thu Oct 13 09:59:24 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Frontend Developer","location":"Amsterdam or Rotterdam","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><b>Do you want to get your hands dirty in our quest to build the best recruitment marketing software in the universe and beyond? You\u2019re an experienced Frontend Developer ready to build a solid product that dazzles users. Does this sounds appealing to you? Then apply for Senior Frontend Developer and get the chance to work in a team that open sources core tools and applies best practices.</p>\n\n<p>Senior Frontend Developer</b><br>\n<i>Rotterdam and / or Amsterdam, fulltime position (32 - 40)</i></p>\n\n<p><b>Description</b><br>\nAs our Senior Frontend Developer you&#39;ll be leading critical product development efforts and get your hands dirty in the frontend implementation of our core platform. You&#39;ll care about the realization of user experience that make our end users life easier. Make tools people love to use.</p>\n\n<p>You can be based either in Amsterdam or Rotterdam. The choice is yours. You&#39;ll be working closely with our CTO and our product development team (with team members on both locations).</p>\n\n<p><b>What you actually do</b><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Deliver frontend experiences worthy of enterprise delight</li>\n<li>Deliver actionable data visualizations that excite</li>\n<li>Be responsible for the choice of the right FE libraries and the realisation of a solid frontend architecture</li>\n<li>Enable development process improvements through tools and automation (pair up with our DevOps and implement CI...yes... also for the frontend assets)</li>\n<li>Safe-guard our enterprise product quality</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Which boxes do you tick?</b><br>\n(Psst...You do not need to tick all the boxes below in order to apply...)\nWhat you see below, paints the ideal picture. Obviously, we also work well with people that have appetite to excel, foundation to build on and potential to succeed.</p>\n\n<p><i>&quot;Our perfect picture&quot;:</i><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor degree or equivalent relevant work experience</li>\n<li>Experience with Agile methodologies (Scrum / Kanban)</li>\n<li>Product development experience - knowing what it takes to build a future-proof product...</li>\n<li>Fan and evangelizer of solid development practices (TDD, CI, etc.) for frontend assets</li>\n<li>Experience with rolling out products to production (incl. proper version mngt, minification, dependencies mngt, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience leading development efforts and aligning with BE engineers &amp; UX designers</li>\n<li>Have worked before in distributed team is a plus</li>\n<li>Love to code FE logic (weapons of choice: JavaScript mainstream libraries like Angular, highcharts, D3.js, flux are in your armory)</li>\n<li>Love to build beautiful extensible things (master in CSS3, mainstream libraries/frameworks like bootstrap, sass are in your toolbox)</li>\n<li>Experience with FE QA (selenium, karma, jasmine, phantomjs etc, or similar etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience with data visualization projects is a big plus</li>\n<li>Have delivered omni-device implementations before</li>\n<li>Comfortable owning the FE test bed</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills in English</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Things we cherish</b><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Business-focus</li>\n<li>Entrepreneurial spirit</li>\n<li>Affinity for detail</li>\n<li>Technical curiosity</li>\n<li>Good communicator</li>\n<li>Pragmatism</li>\n<li>Goal driven personality</li>\n<li>Lame jokes (what can I say...) &amp; beer on Fridays ;-)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>What\u2019s in it for you</b><br>\nFirst of all, you\u2019ll be working with experienced colleagues with a strong vision on web development and software architecture, giving you a full intellectual challenge every day. Secondly, every two weeks you\u2019ll have dedicated R&amp;D time to move the development of our Job Marketing Platform to the next level. Thirdly, you&#39;ll participate to meetups/conferences.</p>\n\n<p><b>What\u2019s more</b><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Laptop of your preferences and two extra screens on your desk</li>\n<li>Flexible working hours</li>\n<li>Time and budget for training</li>\n<li>5 weeks paid holiday per year</li>\n<li>Good salary and additional incentives</li>\n<li>Fixed term contract with an option for perm</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>So, does this sounds appealing to you?</b><br>\nPlease apply by clicking <a href=\"https://vonq.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/senior_frontend_developer_amsterdam/115457/V819/apply\">here</a>. </p>\n\n<p>If you have any questions, please send an e-mail to Dimitra Retsina (CTO/CPO) -&gt; dimitra(at)vonq.com.</p>\n\n<p><b>About VONQ &amp; Job Marketing Platform</b><br>\nYou will be contributing to our flagship product called Job Marketing Platform (JMP). It\u2019s a (big) data-driven application with a recommendation engine to serve multiple personas. JMP incorporates the team\u2019s learnings and best practices including CQRS and event sourcing. Although it\u2019s a young product we\u2019re practicing LEAN methodology to gradually evolve it in a modular way and having a very ambitious roadmap in mind.</p>\n\n<p><b><i>Agency calls not appreciated.</b></p>\n\n<p>Keywords: Job vacancy, Full-time, Rotterdam, Amsterdam, frontend, product Engineer, flux, Angular, react.</i></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://vonq.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/senior_frontend_developer_amsterdam/115457/V819/apply\">Click here to apply!</a></p>\n","company":"VONQ","company_url":"https://vonq.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/s/115457/V819/apply","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/043d1b9e-9127-11e6-921d-c300166686f0.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/0cd2f3aa-9127-11e6-80a7-ba0fc907dd8a"},{"id":"8f17ceda-90cd-11e6-9424-48490c2a4e3e","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 23:36:28 UTC 2016","title":"Software Engineer","location":"Redwood City, CA ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>Our Vision:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Empower humankind to innovate faster, perform better, and solve bigger problems than ever before.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Our mission:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Become the de-facto system of record for enterprise business processes.</p>\n\n<p>When customers deploy Progressly to run their most business critical functions--they put their trust in us. We strive to design and build software that is robust to enterprise standards--blazing fast, reliable, and secure, yet also simple, beautiful, and easy to use.</p>\n\n<p>Are you a full-stack engineer who shares the same vision? Are you up to pushing yourself to the next level of mastery? Come and help us build software people are using every day to push their businesses faster than ever before.</p>\n\n<p><strong>YOU:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Are a great coder! </p></li>\n<li><p>Have practical experience working on a full-stack, scalable, cloud-based system in a fast moving, iterative environment </p></li>\n<li><p>Have top-notch software design skills and sensibilities </p></li>\n<li><p>Constantly learn from experience, quantitative data, and own your decisions </p></li>\n<li><p>Cultivate a collaborative, team-first mindset </p></li>\n<li><p>Have a degree in CS or equivalent experience </p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We are looking to fill roles across product and platform. Whether you are a great backend engineer, a top-notch web developer, or a jack of all trades--we\u2019d love to talk to you.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Our story:</strong> \nProgressly is the new standard for how teams find and execute business processes. Our platform is the world\u2019s only complete solution for all processes across an entire company. Progressly provides a standard format for mission-critical information along with real-time insights that have the power to streamline operations. No matter what type of business you run, Progressly empowers you to move forward faster than ever before.</p>\n\n<p>Based in downtown Redwood City, CA, Progressly was founded by Nick Candito and Clarence Wooten and is backed by investors from 8VC, Accelerate-IT Ventures (AITV), Chicago Ventures, and Palantir.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Visit <a href=\"https://progressly.com/engineering?utm_source=stackoverflow\">our website</a> to learn more!</p>\n","company":"Progressly","company_url":"https://progressly.com/engineering","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/f9ae22b8-90cc-11e6-9733-95a68374a01a.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/8f17ceda-90cd-11e6-9424-48490c2a4e3e"},{"id":"c8c70db6-90ce-11e6-82cf-df239fbac223","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 22:54:30 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Ruby on Rails Developer","location":"Remote - U.S. Based","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>FlexJobs is the leading job service for jobs that offer work flexibility. Our purpose is to make it easier, faster, and safer for people to find professional remote, part-time, freelance, flexible, or alternative schedule jobs. We believe that the job-search experience in general is pretty terrible, and there are big opportunities to 