trong>Other Requirements</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>You must have a reliable development environment including: high-speed Internet access, a fast computer, and phone access</p></li>\n<li><p>Your work environment must be one in which you can really focus without distractions</p></li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>If this is sounding a lot like you, then please consider applying! What we\u2019ll need from you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>An intro email/cover letter telling us why you are the right developer for FlexJobs - don&#39;t forget to tell us about your remote work experience</p></li>\n<li><p>A current resume in .doc, .docx, .pdf, markdown, or .txt</p></li>\n<li><p>Applications can be sent by email to jobs at flexjobs dot com</p></li>\n</ul>\n","company":"FlexJobs","company_url":"http://www.flexjobs.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/a2c9aa92-90ce-11e6-8938-6c2f5ebd0af2.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/c8c70db6-90ce-11e6-82cf-df239fbac223"},{"id":"4fdd7556-90c5-11e6-9b16-857bf27c342d","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 21:48:04 UTC 2016","title":"Full Stack Engineer","location":"Los Angeles","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Job Description\nYou are a full stack engineer with extensive Javascript experience. You&#39;ve scaled teams and products before, and have a desire to join a fast-growing company and make a difference. You will be a part of the core engineering team at Honey, responsible for building new features and maintaining all parts of the core product. This includes backend web development (our main app is a Node.js/Express app tied to MySQL/Elastic/Redis datastores), frontend development (React/Flux), and browser extension development. Most of our code is Coffeescript, but a knowledge of HTML/CSS/Javascript is a big plus.</p>\n\n<p>Preferred Qualifications\nExperience developing and maintaining production web or mobile applications.\nExperience with Node.js/Express.\nSome experience with frontend frameworks (React, Backbone, Angular, etc).\nComfortable with one of SQL, Elastic, or Redis.\nSelf-motivated to build and iterate in quick cycles.\nExperience with git or other version control.</p>\n\n<p>Checkout our perks at <a href=\"http://www.joinhoney.com/careers\">www.joinhoney.com/careers</a></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"mailto:careers@joinhoney.com\">careers@joinhoney.com</a></p>\n","company":"Honey","company_url":"http://www.joinhoney.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/4625efc0-90c5-11e6-9c1f-dc887943b2d6.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/4fdd7556-90c5-11e6-9b16-857bf27c342d"},{"id":"14ce2c52-9099-11e6-8d84-08a17554baaa","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 16:29:43 UTC 2016","title":"Principal Engineer","location":"New York, NY, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><p><strong>Why SecurityScorecard</strong><br>At SecurityScorecard, we are committed to our people and our products. We believe that this commitment will provide the long term outcome that our employees and investors are so excited about. The traction our products, business, and culture have achieved since our founding in 2013 are evidence that we are on the right trajectory. We are looking for the right Technical Project Manager to help us maintain our trajectory.</p><p><strong>Our products and our company</strong><br>The SecurityScorecard ratings platform helps enterprises across the globe manage the cyber security posture of their vendors. Our SaaS products have created a new category of enterprise software and our culture has helped us be recognized as one of the 10 hottest SaaS startups in NY for two years in a row. Our investors include both Sequoia and Google Ventures. We are scaling quickly but are ever mindful of our people and products as we grow.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul> <li>    <p>Provide technical leadership and mentorship to the existing engineering team.</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Leverage cutting-edge technologies to support new and existing and services and processes.</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>Quickly and efficiently design and implement in an agile environment</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Work with other team members to implement consistent architecture</p>    </li>   <li>    <p>Drive projects through all stages of development</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Actively share knowledge and responsibility with other team members and teams\u00a0</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Improve the effective output of the engineering team by managing quality, and identifying inconsistencies.\u00a0\u00a0</p>   </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul> <li>    <p>7+ years of experience with proven experience as a technical leader and mentoring junior to mid-level engineers in a rapidly-growing start-up or organization.</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>3+ years of professional Scala\u00a0experience in a commercial environment. Security experience a must.</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Strong understanding of Software Architecture principals and patterns.</p>   </li>   <li>    <p>Quick-thinker that takes ownership and pride in their work, and is very passionate about technology.</p> </li>   <li>    <p>A commitment and drive for excellence and continual improvement and a strong sense of adventure, excitement and enthusiasm.</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Participate in technical staff augmentation by interviewing and helping to make decisions around prospective hires.</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Experience building and consuming REST services.</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Excellent systems analytical, problem solving and interpersonal skills.</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Bachelor&#39;s degree (CS, EE or Math preferred) or equivalent work experience as well as interest in a fast paced, complex environment.</p> </li>   <li>    <p>Experience working with 3rd party software and libraries, including open source</p>  </li>   <li>    <p>Experience with Postgres.</p>    </li></ul><h3>\u00a0</h3> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FgaT\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7Fgad\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7Fgad</a></p>\n","company":"SecurityScorecard","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/14ce2c52-9099-11e6-8d84-08a17554baaa"},{"id":"6aca0bb8-9098-11e6-9c51-17bfcdd6d183","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 16:24:58 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Software Engineer","location":"New York, NY, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><p><strong>Why SecurityScorecard</strong><br>At SecurityScorecard, we are committed to our people and our products. We believe that this commitment will provide the long term outcome that our employees and investors are so excited about. The traction our products, business, and culture have achieved since our founding in 2013 are evidence that we are on the right trajectory. We are looking for the right Technical Project Manager to help us maintain our trajectory.</p><p><strong>Our products and our company</strong><br>The SecurityScorecard ratings platform helps enterprises across the globe manage the cyber security posture of their vendors. Our SaaS products have created a new category of enterprise software and our culture has helped us be recognized as one of the 10 hottest SaaS startups in NY for two years in a row. Our investors include both Sequoia and Google Ventures. We are scaling quickly but are ever mindful of our people and products as we grow.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul> <li>Leverage cutting-edge technologies to support new and existing and services and processes.</li> <li>Quickly and efficiently design and implement in an agile environment</li>   <li>Work with other team members to implement consistent architecture</li>  <li>Drive projects through all stages of development</li>   <li>Actively share knowledge and responsibility with other team members and teams</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:\u00a0</strong></p><ul>  <li>5+ years of experience as a software engineer; 3+ years of professional Scala experience in a commercial environment.</li>  <li>Security or Network experience strongly preferred.</li> <li>Fast learner that takes ownership and pride in their work and is very passionate about technology</li>  <li>Experience building and consuming REST services.</li>   <li>Solid foundation in computer science fundamentals from data structures and algorithms to high-level design patterns</li>    <li>Excellent systems analytical, problem solving and technical skills</li> <li>Bachelor&#39;s degree (CS, EE or Math preferred) or equivalent work experience as well as interest in a fast paced, complex environment.</li>   <li>Experience working with 3rd party software and libraries, including open source</li>    <li>Experience with design patterns and multi-threading</li>    <li>Experience with Postgres</li></ul> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FgZV\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FgZf\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FgZf</a></p>\n","company":"SecurityScorecard","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/6aca0bb8-9098-11e6-9c51-17bfcdd6d183"},{"id":"13d1b06e-901a-11e6-91ac-f4620bc127a2","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 01:22:19 UTC 2016","title":"Web Developer / Senior Web Developer","location":"Brisbane, Queensland, Australia","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>At The University of Queensland Library we work with cutting edge technology and only look to make our platform better each day! Servicing up to 70K users each day the Library provides a range of services to its customers, maintaining traditional library services as well as implementing new technologies in service delivery and the provision of information skills programs to a variety of clients. The Library is a major user of information technology within The University of Queensland, and designs, develops and hosts a number of very heavily used web applications critical to the UQ scholarly experience.</p>\n\n<p>The role: The successful appointee will design, develop, build and support leading edge and elegant features and applications that benefit a large and diverse community of users. You will become part of a highly motivated development team.</p>\n\n<p>As a Web Developer / Senior web developer, you will:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Undertake the design, development, documentation and management of significant IT projects</li>\n<li>Diagnose, document and respond to very complex problems and faults</li>\n<li>Work as an integral part of the DevOps team</li>\n<li>Mentor, assist and train other developers (HEW 7 Senior Developer)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Our platform is built on industry-leading technologies resulting in a robust and highly maintainable software stack:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Core back-end technologies include PHP, Laravel</li>\n<li>Core front-end technologies include AngularJS, PolymerJS, HTML5, CSS3</li>\n<li>Interoperability technologies include SOAP, JSON, REST, SAML, XML, LDAP</li>\n<li>Continuous integration and deployment uses PHPUnit, BeHat, NightwatchJS, Web Component Tester, SauceLabs, Selenium, NewRelic, Codeship with Docker support</li>\n<li>Web services layer is deployed to Amazon EC2 ECS and frontend is deployed to S3, AWS Aurora and DynamoDB for database support</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>See position description for the full duties at <a href=\"http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer\">http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The person: This position is broad-banded across HEW Levels 6 and 7. Applicants will need to assess their qualifications and experience against the relevant HEW Level Selection Criteria and then nominate the HEW Level they are applying for and address the associated criteria.\nYou will have a relevant Degree or equivalent combination of relevant experience and/or education/training as well as demonstrated strong expertise in web development using PHP.  You will have significant experience with some of: PHP, MySQL, Smarty, JQuery, Github, Amazon Web Services, Continuous Delivery, Behaviour Driven Design, Behat, Agile Project Methodologies and collaboration with Open Source communities.  You will have excellent communication skills and the ability to work to objectives either independently or as a member of a small team.  See the selection criteria for further requirements.</p>\n\n<p>The University of Queensland values diversity and inclusion. Applications are particularly encouraged from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples.</p>\n\n<p>Remuneration: This is a continuing full time appointment (36:15 hours per week) at HEW Level 6 or 7. The remuneration package will be in the range AUD$72,045 - $86,950 p.a., plus employer superannuation contributions of 17% (total package will be in the range AUD$84,293 - $101,732 p.a.). For an appointment of a Senior Web Developer, an attractive remuneration package may be negotiated upon appointment and will be commensurate with the successful applicant&#39;s qualifications and experience.</p>\n\n<p>The University of Queensland also has a wide range of benefits that enhance the working environment and the lives of UQ employees. UQ can offer flexible working arrangements and highly competitive leave options. At UQ staff have access to a broad range of professional and career development schemes to enhance knowledge and skills.</p>\n\n<p>Enquiries: To discuss this role please contact Janna Malikova, telephone +61-7-3346-9886 or email j.malikova@library.uq.edu.au. To submit an application for this role, go to <a href=\"http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer\">http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer</a> and use the Apply button. All applicants must supply the following documents: Resume and a response addressing your suitability to the Selection Criteria (no more than two pages).</p>\n\n<p>Applications close: 9 November 2016 </p>\n\n<p>Job no: 499593</p>\n\n<p>The University of Queensland values diversity and inclusion.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>To submit an application for this role, go to <a href=\"http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer\">http://jobs.uq.edu.au/caw/en/job/499593/web-developersenior-web-developer</a> and use the Apply button.</p>\n","company":"THE UNIVERSITY OF QUEENSLAND LIBRARY","company_url":"https://www.library.uq.edu.au","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/01e91388-901a-11e6-99cb-39b76dd59361.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/13d1b06e-901a-11e6-91ac-f4620bc127a2"},{"id":"9c2e79d0-794d-11e6-88c2-c326e04521d1","created_at":"Wed Oct 12 01:01:32 UTC 2016","title":"Database Infrastructure Engineer - Elasticsearch","location":"Remote","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>GitHub is looking to hire a Database Infrastructure Engineer who wants to build, maintain and scale our Elasticsearch clusters.</p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re looking for someone with proven experience managing the growth of highly resilient search deployments through automation, performance monitoring and optimization. This person will also join our database infrastructure on-call rotation after a training period. We expect this person to be able to demonstrate an expert understanding of search infrastructure, especially Elasticsearch, and have knowledge of the best practice patterns involved in working at a large scale.</p>\n\n<p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Significant experience with distributed search infrastructure (especially Elasticsearch)</p></li>\n<li><p>Strong familiarity with scripting/automation</p></li>\n<li><p>Strong understanding of monitoring and troubleshooting</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with operations in a large production environment</p></li>\n<li><p>Strong written communication</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>NICE TO HAVE:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Experience working with Ruby on Rails</p></li>\n<li><p>On-call experience</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with MySQL, Redis and/or Memcached</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with Git and GitHub</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We want to build the tools that we&#39;ve always dreamed of having, as developers. What tools do you dream of? Come help us build them!</p>\n\n<p>GitHub is committed to building a diverse workforce and strongly encourages applications from people of color and other groups currently underrepresented in tech. We are looking for candidates who:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Display a strong commitment to building an inclusive tech environment</p></li>\n<li><p>Have demonstrated resilience and resourcefulness both in and outside of the workplace</p></li>\n<li><p>Can bring a new perspective based on unique educational, professional, and lived experiences</p></li>\n<li><p>Can effectively communicate with people from disparate backgrounds</p></li>\n<li><p>Have experience mentoring/coaching/teaching, particularly in environments with diverse students/participants</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>WHO WE ARE</strong></p>\n\n<p>GitHub is the best place to share code with friends, co-workers, classmates, and complete strangers. Over ten million people use GitHub to build amazing things together. With the collaborative features of GitHub.com, our desktop and mobile apps, and GitHub Enterprise, it has never been easier for individuals and teams to write better code, faster.</p>\n\n<p>We have a lot of exciting things to do, and we\u2019re looking for the right people to grow with us!</p>\n\n<p><strong>WHY YOU SHOULD JOIN</strong></p>\n\n<p>Working at GitHub is, to put it simply, a special slice of the universe. We&#39;re committed to transparency, collaboration, experimentation, and always staying classy.</p>\n\n<p>Because of this unique perspective, we&#39;ve established one of the most flexible and well designed physical workspaces around that encourages you to work as you work best. Right now, over 60% of our employees are based outside of our San Francisco (SOMA) headquarters and work according to how they get their best stuff done.</p>\n\n<p>Ensuring that GitHubbers are healthy, motivated, focused and creative is how GitHub stays awesome. Part of this is ensuring that our benefits* are out of this world.</p>\n\n<p>In a nutshell, we&#39;ve built and are growing a place where we truly love working, and we think you will too.</p>\n\n<p>GitHub is made up of people with many different backgrounds and lifestyles, and we like it that way. We invite applications from people of all stripes. We don&#39;t discriminate against employees or applicants based on gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, race, religion, age, national origin, citizenship, pregnancy status, veteran status, or any other differences that people imagine to discriminate against one another. Also, if you have a disability, please let us know if there&#39;s anything we can do to make the interview process better for you; we&#39;re happy to accommodate.</p>\n\n<p>*Please note that benefits vary by country, if you have any questions don&#39;t hesitate to ask your recruiter!</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Apply on our <a href=\"https://jobs.lever.co/github/62542da5-0ba0-4ba4-a519-2a5f77b0bdf4\">Careers Page</a></p>\n","company":"GitHub","company_url":"https://jobs.lever.co/github/62542da5-0ba0-4ba4-a519-2a5f77b0bdf4","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/8b7ebf6e-794d-11e6-922f-4defa8de8ab6.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/9c2e79d0-794d-11e6-88c2-c326e04521d1"},{"id":"a7af2516-8ff5-11e6-81c2-e962dcbf5438","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 20:59:52 UTC 2016","title":"Solutions Architect","location":"San Francisco, CA, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><h3><strong>About Us:</strong></h3><p>500friends enables CMOs of major brands to increase their customer lifetime value. Our SaaS lifecycle marketing suite, LoyaltyPlus, makes it easy to execute omni-channel loyalty programs while incentivizing customer identification, creating a single view of all customer interactions across channels, and executing personalized customer retention campaigns. Our services surrounding LoyaltyPlus span across strategic consulting, platform integration and implementation, program management and support, and advanced analytics. Our top clients include Abercrombie &amp; Fitch, 1-800-Flowers, Pittsburgh Steelers, New Balance, and L&#39;Oreal.\u00a0We were recently <a href=\"http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160105005917/en/500friends-Merkle-Company-Named-Leader-Customer-Loyalty\">ranked a &quot;Leader</a>&quot;, the highest ranking, in The Forrester Wave: Customer Loyalty Solutions for Midsize Organizations.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.merkleinc.com/news-and-events/press-releases/2014/merkle-acquires-omnichannel-loyalty-solution-provider-500friends\">We were acquired by Merkle</a> at the end of 2014, a $400M+ (revenues), privately held performance marketing agency that is majority owned by Dentsu Aegis Network, but 500friends is our own operating group. This means that you essentially get to join a start-up with the security and stability of an established company.\u00a0</p><p>Our approach to hiring:\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/stop-hunting-unicorns-justin-yoshimura?published=u\">Stop Hunting Unicorns</a></p><h3><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></h3><p>The Solutions Architect will play a critical role in managing the on-boarding of new customers as well as facilitating the roll-out of complex technical features for existing customers. As one of the main points of contact for our most strategic accounts, this is a highly visible role with significant ownership. This person will have considerable influence on the future of our product by acting as the voice for their clients.</p><h3><u><strong>You will:</strong></u></h3><ul>  <li>Lead deployments and retain ownership for the overall planning, coordination and delivery of our SAAS platform for sophisticated, multi-channel retailers</li>  <li>Run multiple technical projects and/or implementations simultaneously</li>  <li>Work closely with internal cross-functional teams including Engineering, Client Success, Strategy and Product</li>  <li>Work closely with technical resources from client teams, to include managing external technical vendor relationships on the client\u2019s behalf</li>  <li>Identify, manage, and resolve technical challenges faced throughout deployment process</li> <li>Ensure projects are clearly scoped, well-managed, delivered on time, and positioned for long-term success</li></ul><h3><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></h3><p>You have an engineering background and have been client-facing for the past four years. You have done considerable integration and API work. You enjoy and have the patience for working with non-technical people. You\u2019re ready and excited to take on complete ownership of client engagements.\u00a0</p><ul>   <li>BA/BS degree in a technical field\u00a0or equivalent practical\u00a0experience</li> <li>5-10 years of hands-on experience in delivery and implementation of internet products and technologies</li> <li>Demonstrated experience in managing large IT projects</li>  <li>Strong analysis skills, ability to evaluate customer requirements and modify existing solution</li> <li>Experience in integrating systems using APIs</li>   <li>Track record of ensuring the highest levels of customer satisfaction</li>   <li>Domain knowledge in eCommerce</li>  <li>Ability to architect and built solutions for our customers.\u00a0</li></ul> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FcZH\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FcZR\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FcZR</a></p>\n","company":"500friends","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/a7af2516-8ff5-11e6-81c2-e962dcbf5438"},{"id":"715de6a8-8fe3-11e6-8228-a3ac09942eca","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 18:51:41 UTC 2016","title":"Full Stack Engineer","location":"SF & Santa Cruz","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>WHO WE ARE</strong></p>\n\n<p>Looker is on a mission to bring better insights and data-driven decisions to every business. Everything we do is aimed at making sure our customers love every aspect of Looker, from our products and technologies to our ease of doing business and our support.  We are looking for curiously brilliant individuals to join our team as we reinvent data analytics.  Get data-driven and see yourself at Looker. </p>\n\n<p><strong>WHAT WE&#39;VE GOT GOING ON</strong></p>\n\n<p>The engineering team at Looker is a tight-knit group of high-performers. We value simplicity in both our code and our user interfaces. We don\u2019t believe in large teams; we opt for small, diverse groups that move fast, communicate clearly and achieve more.  We try to choose the right tool for the job, not one tool to solve all problems. We make a huge impact on product direction, we experiment, and we iterate rapidly.</p>\n\n<p>Looker is seeking experienced Full Stack Engineers to build out our cutting-edge data discovery platform. Looker is still a small team, so you\u2019ll have the opportunity to work on many aspects of the product.  Actually, you\u2019ll probably work on nearly all of it! You should have extensive experience and a proven track record solving web, database, and network engineering problems. Most of all, you should share a love of programming.</p>\n\n<p><strong>WHAT WE NEED YOU TO DO</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Love building new technologies that have the power to impact businesses\u2019 day-to-day operations and change the way companies make decisions. </li>\n<li>Love working with a small team of highly-motivated individuals.</li>\n<li>Possess innate passion for coding, building businesses, web development, and data.</li>\n<li>Solve complex web engineering problems.<br></li>\n<li>Be a teacher, mentor and foster a collegial atmosphere while giving and receiving feedback.<br></li>\n<li>Take full ownership.  Make Looker better.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>WHAT YOU BRING TO LOOKER</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>5+ years experience building highly-available, modern web applications.</li>\n<li>A firm grasp of Computer Science fundamentals including object oriented design, data structures, algorithm design, problem solving and complexity analysis. </li>\n<li>Expert knowledge of modern JavaScript, HTML, &amp; CSS, including libraries and frameworks.</li>\n<li>Deep familiarity with at least one of these server side languages: Ruby, Python, Java, or similar.</li>\n<li>Interest in working on or debugging many layers of the application stack, including issues as far-ranging as SSH tunnels to Java stack overflow exceptions.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of how to identify, prevent, and resolve security issues in all layers of the application stack. </li>\n<li>Authorization to work in the U.S. without visa sponsorship.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>NICE TO HAVE</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Past experience working in startups, building information visualizations, and/or experience with BI and data discovery tools.</li>\n<li>Experience managing databases and familiarity writing SQL queries.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Hiring experienced Full Stack Engineers in both our SF and SC offices.  Interested in learning more about Looker?  Visit <a href=\"https://looker.com/company/team\">here</a>\nApply <a href=\"https://jobs.lever.co/looker?by=team\">here</a></p>\n","company":"Looker","company_url":"https://looker.com/","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/ad5fd54a-8fe2-11e6-8e6e-be94e858740e.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/715de6a8-8fe3-11e6-8228-a3ac09942eca"},{"id":"5985a9b4-8fe1-11e6-9aea-f397c02af888","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 18:36:08 UTC 2016","title":"Full Stack Engineer","location":"Chicago, il","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Interested in working on a scalable SaaS application from end to end?\nWe&#39;re looking for a full stack engineer to be part of our growing core team. You&#39;ll work on everything from front-end styling to server-side logic to writing unit tests.\nYou&#39;ll work with Product Managers and Designers to determine functionality and look and feel.\nYou should be able to debug problems at every level of the stack, from browser to application, database and server.\nAs a full stack engineer you will play an important role in helping to develop a highly scalable SaaS application. You must have solid communication skills, be detail oriented, show leadership and an exemplary work ethic. </p>\n\n<p>REQUIRED SKILLS</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience writing applications using MVC frameworks</li>\n<li>MySQL experience</li>\n<li>Expert at object-oriented programming concepts and design patterns</li>\n<li>Portfolio and code samples showing work that demonstrates OOP concepts</li>\n<li>HTML, CSS and Javascript</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of Git</li>\n<li>LAMP server administration</li>\n<li>Front-end and back-end development experience</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>HELPFUL IF YOU HAVE</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A passion for web development and an interest in sharing that with others</li>\n<li>Demonstrated ability to develop highly scalable Web applications</li>\n<li>Experience with AWS/Azure/RackSpace Cloud/Google Compute</li>\n<li>Experience with other PHP frameworks utilizing the MVC design pattern</li>\n<li>Linux administration skills</li>\n<li>Front-end development skills</li>\n<li>Most likely the successful candidate will be someone who has a computer science background with considerable industry experience.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>COMPENSATION</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>We offer a competitive salary, benefits and bonus structure based on experience and performance.</li>\n<li>We will setup you up with a workstation of your choice and whatever software you need for development.</li>\n<li>We value teamwork, innovation and productivity and foster an exciting and committed work environment that will help you become successful and grow in your position. To apply email resumes to: <a href=\"mailto:jobs@agentisenergy.com\">jobs@agentisenergy.com</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Agentis Energy is an equal opportunity employer.</p>\n\n<p>EEO Employer. No recruiters or phone calls, please.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>To apply email resumes to: <a href=\"mailto:jobs@agentisenergy.com\">jobs@agentisenergy.com</a></p>\n","company":"Agentis Energy","company_url":"http://www.agentisenergy.com/","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/4c3ac56e-8fe1-11e6-9cc6-abeec69b873b.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/5985a9b4-8fe1-11e6-9aea-f397c02af888"},{"id":"eb44e0dc-8fe0-11e6-8aa6-e6c044fa4ab9","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 18:32:25 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Software Engineer ","location":"San Francisco, CA","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>SS&amp;C Advent, a leading provider of award-winning software and services for the global investment management industry, is seeking a Senior Software Engineer to work in our San Francisco office. We are looking for a passionate, driven, and diligent software engineer for our Geneva Product Development group. </p>\n\n<p>As a key member of our middle-tier development team, you are expected to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Participate in full development life cycle.</li>\n<li>Participate in sprint planning</li>\n<li>Work with business analyst in defining and analyzing requirements</li>\n<li>Work with architects and lead engineers in defining architecture.</li>\n<li>Implement key modules as per development guidelines.</li>\n<li>Work with QA team for validating software functionality</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Required Skills/Experience</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>10+ year of software development experience</li>\n<li>5+ year of Java server side development experience</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of various Java specifications, frameworks and libraries: Spring, Hibernate, DropWizard, JMS, JPA, etc</li>\n<li>Experience implementing REST APIs and SOAP APIs</li>\n<li>Experience implementing reusable components and libraries</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of Object Oriented Design and Development</li>\n<li>Experience working with relational database systems and NoSQL database systems.</li>\n<li>Strong computer science fundamentals: data structures, algorithms, distributed systems, Network Communication</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of software architectures: Distributed, Client Server, SOA, and Multi-tier.</li>\n<li>Experience working in Agile/Scrum environment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Strongly Recommended</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience working with build and automation tools and libraries ( Maven/Gradle , Jenkins, Chef, etc)</li>\n<li>Experience implementing concurrent, fault tolerant and scalable system</li>\n<li>Experience working with message oriented middleware</li>\n<li>Knowledge and understanding of IAAS,  PAAS and SAAS</li>\n<li>Experience working with any leading IAAS platform</li>\n<li>Experience working with any leading PAAS platform</li>\n<li>Experience working with Docker</li>\n<li>Experience with Microsoft technology stack ( C#, .net framework, ASP.NET, WCF, etc)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Education</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor in Science/ Engineering preferred</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>SS&amp;C Advent is an equal opportunity employer, committed to a diverse workforce.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://app.jobvite.com/j?cj=o86d3fwe&s=GitHub\">Click here to apply</a></p>\n","company":"Advent Software","company_url":"http://www.advent.com/","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/76a7efb2-8fe0-11e6-8742-f792c906d49b.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/eb44e0dc-8fe0-11e6-8aa6-e6c044fa4ab9"},{"id":"63836590-8fce-11e6-8784-8bdf2faf7961","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 16:19:25 UTC 2016","title":"Front End Developer","location":"Toronto","type":"Full Time","description":"<h2>ABOUT US</h2>\n\n<p>Mavencare is a Toronto-based digital health startup company whose goal is to make finding high-quality caregivers simple, intuitive, convenient, transparent and human. Our Vision is to revolutionize home health care; to create a world where people can live out their lives in the comfort of their own homes. We believe that we are just at the beginning of an opportunity to use technological innovation to reshape health care delivery for an aging population!</p>\n\n<p>Want to work on a product that helps families keep their loved ones happy and healthy at home as they age? Join our Product Development team as a Front End Developer, building great software for our customers and staff. You&#39;ll work with world-class engineers on a team that ships every week. You will learn, embrace, and extend the development patterns and design principles that make our products a joy to use. As a member of our agile team, you&#39;ll tackle aggressive sprint schedules married with design thinking to deliver outstanding experiences, but you&#39;ll also have dedicated time for high level explorations and cross disciplinary collaboration with sales, recruiting, logistics and UX teams.</p>\n\n<h2>RESPONSIBILITIES</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build elegant and intuitive user interfaces</li>\n<li>Estimate tasks to facilitate iteration planning</li>\n<li>Develop HTML/CSS/Javascript to accurately implement web designs with an attention to detail</li>\n<li>Building Responsive and mobile friendly websites\n*Able to deliver and adjust prototypes rapidly to help flesh out requirements</li>\n<li>Able to jump into new problem spaces and quickly identify potential pitfalls in design/implementation or UX</li>\n<li>Can communicate effectively with technical peers as well as people with disparate backgrounds</li>\n<li>Someone who likes to work hands on and be self-directed in a fast paced, free and responsible environment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>At least two years of web application development experience</li>\n<li>A college degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science or similar field, including a solid understanding of Computer Science fundamentals</li>\n<li>JavaScript expert who has developed UIs and frameworks for internal and/or external customers</li>\n<li>Strong proficiency in at least one Javascript framework like Angular, React, Ember or Backbone</li>\n<li>Experience with HTML5, CSS and UI frameworks</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of front end build and management tools like Grunt, Gulp, Bower and RequireJS</li>\n<li>A scrappy, entrepreneurial attitude that gets high-quality projects done quickly</li>\n<li>Familiarity with pieces of our existing stack a plus (Mongo, Express, Angular, Node.js, iOS, Android, JavaScript, React, and more)</li>\n<li>Product sense with a strong command of metrics a strong plus</li>\n<li>Passionate about the healthcare industry</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>BONUS POINTS</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience working with backend engineers to define RESTful APIs and data formats</li>\n<li>Experience with creating and maintaining UI toolkits/frameworks</li>\n<li>Experience shipping consumer apps a strong plus</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of modern web standards</li>\n<li>Experience in creating formalized wireframes, storyboards, user and process flows using prototyping tools\n*Familiarity with a continuous delivery environment using tools like TravisCI or Jenkins</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>OPPORTUNITIES TO</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Learn more about senior care, technology, app development, marketing, business analysis, and the healthcare field</li>\n<li>Gain business and technical experience in a fast-growing start-up</li>\n<li>Become a part of the Mavencare team, which includes free weekly team lunches and monthly team events!</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:mcjobs@mavencare.com\">mcjobs@mavencare.com</a></p>\n","company":"Mavencare Inc.","company_url":"https://www.mavencare.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/551672cc-8fce-11e6-9189-cd1774011aaa.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/63836590-8fce-11e6-8784-8bdf2faf7961"},{"id":"c22936fe-8f6c-11e6-8a0b-22ef10d3d638","created_at":"Tue Oct 11 04:40:32 UTC 2016","title":"Full-Stack Engineer","location":"San Francisco","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Come help us build a real-life SimCity. We\u2019re looking for sharp engineers who can work across the stack to improve the world\u2019s first transit planning platform. Our stack is Rails, Python, Javascript (React) and Postgres/PostGIS. You\u2019ll get to work with a smart, collaborative team of six other engineers.</p>\n\n<p>The easiest way to understand what we&#39;re doing is this two minute demo: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o-JpgoUKr5I\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o-JpgoUKr5I</a></p>\n\n<p>You\u2019ll be working on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Building out new features and experiences to help cities make better decisions about public transit</li>\n<li>Building systems to ingest and model transit data</li>\n<li>Continuously improving our performance and user experience</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You\u2019d be a good fit if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You\u2019ve built high-quality products before.</li>\n<li>You have experience working across the web stack, and thinking about how to architect systems</li>\n<li>You\u2019re resourceful \u2014 we\u2019re a small company, and you\u2019ll do a bit of everything</li>\n<li>Making cities better excites you</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>To apply, email <a href=\"mailto:jobs@getremix.com\">jobs@getremix.com</a> with a resume and a few words on why you&#39;re right for the role.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>To apply, email <a href=\"mailto:jobs@getremix.com\">jobs@getremix.com</a> with a resume and a few words on why you&#39;re right for the role.</p>\n","company":"Remix","company_url":"http://getremix.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/8fcee60e-8f6c-11e6-9ed7-50c4e3013d74.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/c22936fe-8f6c-11e6-8a0b-22ef10d3d638"},{"id":"d33e1b04-8f39-11e6-9200-59a7dd27aaeb","created_at":"Mon Oct 10 22:35:42 UTC 2016","title":"iOS/Swift Developer @ Breadwallet","location":"Remote","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Breadwallet is looking for an experienced software engineer to work with us to build out the future of money. We\u2019re the leading mobile Bitcoin wallet, and need a few more hands to help us achieve our vision: to be the onramp to Bitcoin.</p>\n\n<p>Our team is a group of Bitcoin enthusiasts. We\u2019re geographically distributed across the US and Canada, with a central office in San Francisco, CA. You\u2019ll be working directly with me, @ssutch, to build out the next version of our iOS app in Swift, porting sections of our old codebase in Objective-C when necessary. Our new designs make our app accessible to millions of more users, and takes us beyond the stage of early-adopters.</p>\n\n<p>The most important skillset for this job is iOS and a strong handle on swift. Candidates must have a firm understanding on how modern iOS apps are built and must have worked on them in the past. We seek to build a scaleable codebase that utilizes patterns like Reactive Programming or other alternatives to reliably managing state. Your input on this topic is welcome.</p>\n\n<p>You will not be required to have experience with Bitcoin. Our underlying Bitcoin wallet library is already finished and in use in our Android product (and open source, check us out on Github). There are just a few concepts that must be learned to utilize it.</p>\n\n<p>Experience with Android/Java and Javascript/React is definitely a bonus. Everyone at breadwallet is a polyglot and you are definitely encouraged to try, and learn, new things!</p>\n\n<p>Here are some bullet points that might interest you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Full benefits package</li>\n<li>Work remotely</li>\n<li>New hardware when you need it</li>\n<li>Travel to SF once a year for our team on-site</li>\n<li>Unlimited vacation</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Fill out this form and we will get back to you: <a href=\"https://goo.gl/forms/KU1an9oDCY9CbyK73\">https://goo.gl/forms/KU1an9oDCY9CbyK73</a></p>\n","company":"Breadwallet LLC","company_url":"https://breadwallet.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/bb70a384-8f39-11e6-90b6-5b9247fa279e.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/d33e1b04-8f39-11e6-9200-59a7dd27aaeb"},{"id":"24ee0862-8ef2-11e6-81d5-999dcc0577fe","created_at":"Mon Oct 10 14:06:38 UTC 2016","title":"Android and iOS developers","location":"Bucharest ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Android and iOS developers wanted for world domination, challenging projects. </p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re building an army to conquer the world. The battleground? Mobile phones. Our weapon? Apps. And art. And brains. Lots and lots of brains. </p>\n\n<p>We need passionate, forward-thinking mobile developers to lead the charge! Android, iOS and web. Or a mix. You just gotta love it. </p>\n\n<p>Don\u2019t get scared. If you see this ad and you think you\u2019re not good enough, just stop. You don\u2019t even know how great you can be, in the right context, with the right team, working on the right project. Give it a shot!</p>\n\n<p>Our products (so far)</p>\n\n<p>Stickchat</p>\n\n<p>Visual communication with stickers and gifs has exploded. But language and emotions are so complex that generic sticker packs and gifs cut out from movies just aren\u2019t enough. Dozens of languages, hundreds of expressions, thousands of inside jokes. We\u2019re building original animations for each and every one. Communication through digital art.</p>\n\n<p>Redraw Keyboard</p>\n\n<p>The Android keyboard to rule them all. 1M downloads in 20 days and growing. Hundreds of original themes and stickers. It\u2019s now the best rated third-party keyboard on Google Play. </p>\n\n<p>Themes &amp; live wallpapers</p>\n\n<p>We own the largest portfolio of themes and live wallpapers on Google Play. 500.000 daily downloads. </p>\n\n<p>Let\u2019s get down to business</p>\n\n<p>How does it pay?</p>\n\n<p>That\u2019s up to you. If you\u2019re great, it pays a lot. If you\u2019re not, we\u2019ll help you get there. We never miss payday. Never. No excuses.</p>\n\n<p>What about the hours?</p>\n\n<p>Work smart, not a lot. Get stuff done and hours will never be an issue. And that\u2019s really because work-life balance is bullshit. Life doesn\u2019t pause at 9am and restarts at 5pm. When you\u2019re at work, guess what, life happens, you\u2019re still breathing. It\u2019s still your life and it should damn well be a great one. There\u2019s no excuse for a shitty life at work. Work should mean something to you. Your colleagues should care about you. You should care about what you\u2019re doing and who you\u2019re doing it with. Time doesn\u2019t go backwards so don\u2019t throw it away. Work on something you like. Work on something you care about. Work on your legacy. </p>\n\n<p>How\u2019s the office?</p>\n\n<p>Some people say it\u2019s kinda like Facebook, but better :) We\u2019re located in one of the newest office buildings in Bucharest (Skanska Green Court). It was designed from scratch by a team of young architects and decorators that love T-Me so they put the very sould of the company into every corner. If only for that you should come in to check it out. #nopressure #greatcoffee</p>\n\n<p>How\u2019s the team?</p>\n\n<p>See for yourself. Search for T-Me Studios on LinkedIn and get in touch. Don\u2019t trust me, the writer of this post, ask them directly. They don\u2019t bite ;) Also, our Facebook page does a pretty good job showing how things really are around here. </p>\n\n<p>What else?</p>\n\n<p>At T-Me, your work hits tens of millions of users. That\u2019s a f***ing big party to plan. But everyone can plan a small party. Don\u2019t be everyone. Be special. Be f***ing great, because great people own the world. Don\u2019t settle for less. </p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re probably the biggest mobile publisher in Romania our apps having been installed on more than 160M devices. However, we\u2019re not slowing down, we want to be the biggest in Europe and have a strong say in shaping the digital world.  </p>\n\n<p>T-Me Studios was started by two guys in 2013 at a local Starbucks. Fast forward 3 years, we\u2019re 60+ people, renting a 600-square meter space in one of the newest office buildings in Bucharest, gliding from one corner to another on Segways and scooters. </p>\n\n<p>Wanna be on stage when we tell the story 5 years from now, with our very own F8-style conference? Join us so we can build the next chapters together.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Email your resume at <a href=\"mailto:irina.iancu@timmystudios.com\">irina.iancu@timmystudios.com</a></p>\n","company":"T-Me Studios","company_url":"http://timmystudios.com/auxiliary/comingsoon","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/fc5148b6-8ef0-11e6-9287-6720e6431292.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/24ee0862-8ef2-11e6-81d5-999dcc0577fe"},{"id":"59eecbf0-8ee3-11e6-8dd0-073e59f2a649","created_at":"Mon Oct 10 12:17:09 UTC 2016","title":"Software Developer","location":"Anywhere","type":"Contract","description":"<h2>Description</h2>\n\n<p>R3 Labs are a remote team based predominantly in Europe. We are passionate about the power of automation in cloud environments, and are seeking likeminded developers to join our team working on our opern-source ochestration project - ernest.io.</p>\n\n<p>The ideal candidates will be passionate about software engineering with an understanding not only of the code but also the overall architecture of an asynchronous micro-service oriented platform. </p>\n\n<h2>Your role and responsibilities</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>End-to-end responsibility from technical design to deployment and testing.</li>\n<li>Working hand-in-hand with an awesome team of engineers in an agile software development environment.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Required technical skills &amp; experience</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>3 to 5 years experience as backend software engineer.</li>\n<li>API design experience.</li>\n<li>Experience in unit and functional testing is required.</li>\n<li>Experience working on a continuous integration workflow.</li>\n<li>Ability to work in GNU/Linux environment.</li>\n<li>Experience and clear concepts on developing APIs.</li>\n<li>Experience in Version Control Systems is a must, Git would be highly appreciated.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Personal skills</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Your written and spoken English will be fluent, and you will have a degree in Computer Science or similar experience.</li>\n<li>Demonstrable comfort and productivity working on a distributed team.</li>\n<li>You will be comfortable working in Central European Time.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Preferred skills &amp; abilities</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience building micro-service based platforms.</li>\n<li>Experience of PaaS and/or SaaS environments would be beneficial.</li>\n<li>Experience on maintaining open source products.</li>\n<li>Experience with any statically typed languages is a bonus.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Our stack</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Go, Ruby,  bash...</li>\n<li>Nats.io</li>\n<li>Postgres / Redis</li>\n<li>Docker</li>\n<li>AWS, Google Cloud, Azure, OpenStack, &amp; vCloud</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"mailto:jobs@r3labs.io\">jobs@r3labs.io</a></p>\n","company":"R3 Labs","company_url":"http://r3labs.io","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/d1d8d1b6-8ee2-11e6-832d-3b999e618bbf.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/59eecbf0-8ee3-11e6-8dd0-073e59f2a649"},{"id":"5222c30e-8ce5-11e6-95c7-cccdd3a0dff0","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 23:25:48 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Rails Developer","location":"Cupertino","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Beezwax is a software development agency based in Oakland, with developers located across the Bay Area and beyond. We\u2019ve been in business for 20 years translating client needs into powerful and elegant web, mobile, and database applications. With over 500 clients so far, we\u2019re continually bringing in new projects that challenge our developers to use the full range of their technical abilities and expand their skill sets. We seek out super-smart people with excellent communication skills and proven rock-solid reliability. Beezwax is a highly collaborative and creative work environment that keeps work interesting and engaging.</p>\n\n<p><strong>position</strong></p>\n\n<p>We\u2019re looking for an experienced rails developer to help us turn around a wide variety of client projects. You should be actively engaged and passionate about the technologies you\u2019re using, quick to learn, and excited to collaborate. And you should be inspired by a work environment in which requirements and technologies vary from project to project, driven by a balance of the client\u2019s needs and our expertise and experience.</p>\n\n<p><strong>requirements</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 3, preferably 6 or more, years experience with Rails and community-standard code structure and testing.</li>\n<li>Thorough knowledge of Ruby on Rails</li>\n<li>Commitment to writing well-tested code</li>\n<li>Proficiency with Git</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills</li>\n<li>This is position is located in the South Bay and is not currently available for remote work.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>nice-to-haves</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Familiarity with a front-end framework such as Ember or Angular</li>\n<li>Experience working on a distributed team</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>benefits</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive compensation, including a retirement plan and an excellent healthcare package with vision and dental</li>\n<li>Support for developer productivity and continued learning in the forms of hardware, software, learning materials, training, and conferences</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.</p>\n\n<p>Looking forward to hearing from you!</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.beezwax.net/tellus/jobs/sr-rails-developer\">https://www.beezwax.net/tellus/jobs/sr-rails-developer</a></p>\n","company":"Beezwax Datatools, Inc.","company_url":"http://www.beezwax.net","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/f9d994d4-8ce4-11e6-8327-c3fb375ad09b.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/5222c30e-8ce5-11e6-95c7-cccdd3a0dff0"},{"id":"f46da0bc-8cd0-11e6-94ca-550796864c4c","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 21:00:25 UTC 2016","title":"JavaScript Engineer/Architect","location":"Houston, TX","type":"Contract","description":"<p>&quot;WHAT WE&#39;RE DOING AND WHY WE NEED YOU&quot;</p>\n\n<p>At QRI, we are crafting high-end visualization platforms for each of our patented products. Our fast-paced programming environment is exciting and well integrated, as we work closely with industry experts to deliver meaningful content using the most cutting edge technology the CS world has to offer. As a JavaScript Engineer/Architect, you will immediately jump in to the development process and participate in our weekly sprint cycles. A typical work day could include adding new features to an established UI design, optimizing query logic or database architecture, presenting workflows for improved code structure, supervising usability test labs, researching new libraries and frameworks, and brainstorming new product lifecycles.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;THE BASICS&quot;</p>\n\n<p>BSc (PhD or MSs recommended) with GPA &gt;= 3.5 in Computer Science or related fields.\nSkilled and creative team player also able to work independently in a complex and dynamic environment.\nBe prepared with a demo of recent project work.\nConsiderable experience in the following ...</p>\n\n<p>&quot;TECHNOLOGIES WE LOVE&quot;</p>\n\n<p>Core: JavaScript, ES6</p>\n\n<p>Environment: GitHub, Webpack, Browserify, Grunt, Gulp, NPM, etc.</p>\n\n<p>Server Side: Node, Express, API design (REST or sockets), MySQL, MongoDB</p>\n\n<p>Front End Frameworks: React, Angular 1 or 2, Knockout, Ember, Backbone, or ExtJS</p>\n\n<p>Front End: LESS/SASS/CSS, HTML</p>\n\n<p>Other: Highcharts, OpenLayers</p>\n\n<p>Recommended: share your GitHub profile with us!</p>\n\n<p>&quot;WHAT WE VALUE&quot;</p>\n\n<p>You&#39;re excited to work with others in complex and dynamic systems environments.</p>\n\n<p>You\u2019re not afraid to make mistakes because without challenge, you\u2019re not learning. Oh, and we\u2019re not afraid to let you fail either.</p>\n\n<p>Speaking of learning, you have a constant desire to grow and develop. So do we, and were not afraid to wield the cutting edge of new technology.</p>\n\n<p>You thrive in a fast-paced environment, and take to heart our team motto: 80% accuracy at the speed of light.</p>\n\n<p>You care about great design, not only in the product and visual sense, but also in your code and technical architecture.</p>\n\n<p>You are comfortable with both large-scale and iterative development styles.</p>\n\n<p>You enjoy working with others, but are also an independent programmer.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Apply on our career page:</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.qrigroup.com/careers\">http://www.qrigroup.com/careers</a></p>\n","company":"QRI","company_url":"http://www.qrigroup.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/0ed899da-8cd0-11e6-86de-8c5e40f5e0fb.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/f46da0bc-8cd0-11e6-94ca-550796864c4c"},{"id":"8d4fe9aa-8cce-11e6-9579-923c3f7eb9d3","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 20:43:07 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Backend Developer ","location":"Austin ","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>We&#39;re looking for a seasoned Node.JS JavaScript developer to take the lead on the API and other back-end components of our flagship product, LeadConduit. This is a high-availability platform, responsible for handling expensive data, so we&#39;re looking for someone with experience in similar situations. You will be responsible for technical decisions that directly impact our customers. Working in conjunction with the CTO, Director of Product Management, and the front-end UI development team, you will move our platform into the next phase of its life.</p>\n\n<p>We are a small team of effective developers committed to the potential of our software offerings and the company in general. Each developer has a stake in the direction of our products, the company, and the culture surrounding those things.</p>\n\n<p>What you have...</p>\n\n<p>Working understanding of HTTP and REST</p>\n\n<p>Expert understanding of JavaScript and Node.JS</p>\n\n<p>Expert understanding of NPM modules</p>\n\n<p>Working knowledge of git and GitHub</p>\n\n<p>Experience designing and implementing high-volume, high-availability HTTP APIs using Node.JS</p>\n\n<p>Experience working on a small team, where clear, efficient, and respectful communication is critical</p>\n\n<p>Experience deploying, debugging, fixing, and otherwise supporting production systems</p>\n\n<p>Experience writing API documentation</p>\n\n<p>Operational experience with MongoDB</p>\n\n<p>Experience with automated testing</p>\n\n<p>Experience reviewing GitHub pull requests</p>\n\n<p>Experience working with UI developers</p>\n\n<p>Clear written and verbal communication skills</p>\n\n<p>Clear technical communication</p>\n\n<p>Bonus points for...</p>\n\n<p>Experience working with Online Lead Generation Marketing</p>\n\n<p>What we&#39;re offering...</p>\n\n<p>A financially stable company, with the freedom and opportunities of a startup culture</p>\n\n<p>Flexible work schedule</p>\n\n<p>Unlimited PTO</p>\n\n<p>Live Music Capital Holiday</p>\n\n<p>Beautiful office space in Hyde Park (close to Central Market, Vino Vino, and Hyde Park Gym)</p>\n\n<p>Paid attendance to one tech conference of your choosing per year</p>\n\n<p>Retirement plan matching up to 3% of your salary</p>\n\n<p>Health, dental, vision, disability and life insurance</p>\n\n<p>Medical and Dependent Care FSA available</p>\n\n<p>Fun office environment with Ping pong table, kegerator, and snacks</p>\n\n<p>Remote employment may be an option for this position for the right candidate</p>\n\n<p>ActiveProspect is a marketing Software as a Service (Saas) platform that instantly qualifies internet leads. We help marketers automate their unique processes for acquiring qualified sales leads, building accurate email subscriber lists, and providing superior transparency for legal compliance. Each month, millions of opt-in Internet leads are processed on the ActiveProspect platform on behalf of customers across a wide range of industries. As lead generation innovators, we invented the concept of lead certification to help marketers independently verify the origin and authenticity of Internet leads. Founded in 2004, ActiveProspect is headquartered in Austin, TX.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"http://activeprospect.applytojob.com/apply/27bomm/Senior-JavaScript-Backend-Developer\">http://activeprospect.applytojob.com/apply/27bomm/Senior-JavaScript-Backend-Developer</a></p>\n","company":"ActiveProspect","company_url":"http://ActiveProspect","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/8a76ffde-8cce-11e6-89d8-d7a7a4042e86.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/8d4fe9aa-8cce-11e6-9579-923c3f7eb9d3"},{"id":"a0389ac2-39df-11e6-9bb0-7b3faa3729cc","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 16:49:23 UTC 2016","title":"Full-Stack Engineer (C#, ASP.NET MVC and React)","location":"San Francisco or Remote","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Come help us create the future of Kaggle and in doing so, help shape the future of data science.</p>\n\n<p>As background, Kaggle is best known for running machine learning competitions. We have a community of almost 600K data scientists who come to Kaggle to learn, compete, and collaborate on the cutting edge of machine learning to solve business and research problems for organizations like Facebook, NASA, and GE.</p>\n\n<p>In our next chapter, Kaggle is expanding to become the place where data scientists share code and analysis in a reproducible way. We&#39;re building this platform for data science collaboration (the closest analogy is Github for data science) around our thriving community. As part of our small team, you&#39;ll be a part of designing and building this platform in its early stages. We don&#39;t expect you to know everything coming in, so we&#39;ll pair you with mentors who will help you grow and develop your skills.</p>\n\n<p>We like working remotely: a lot of our team is distributed. We prefer US-based timezones but will hire the right candidate anywhere in the world. If you\u2019re in the San Francisco Bay Area or interested in relocating here, you\u2019ll enjoy our easy-going office culture and all the beauty the Bay Area has to offer.</p>\n\n<p><strong>What you&#39;ll do</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Architect and create new site features, ranging from discussing wireframes to creating the data model and deploying the end result.</li>\n<li>Implement local tooling to facilitate users transferring their analytics between local environments and Kaggle&#39;s infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Build features in our current web stack (C#, ASP.NET MVC,  TypeScript, React, SQL Server, and Azure).</li>\n<li>Create and build on our services layer (which includes Linux,  Docker, and Python for running user code).</li>\n<li>Measure, optimize, and scale Kaggle\u2019s infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Ship every day.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What we&#39;re looking for</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You have solid programming skills from regularly shipping code.</li>\n<li>You have  exposure to web programming and  modern practices.</li>\n<li>You&#39;re experienced with a stack based on C#, ASP.NET MVC, TypeScript, React, SQL Server, and Azure (or are excited to pick it up).</li>\n<li>You\u2019re motivated, self-directed, a good communicator and have strong telecommuting skills (our engineering team is spread around the world).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What will set you apart</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You have a history of open source contributions and helping the broader software engineering community (through Github, StackOverflow, a blog, or the like).</li>\n<li>You are excited about data and curious to learn more about machine learning.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What we offer</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A low ego environment where you can give and receive direct feedback.</li>\n<li>Transparent leadership that openly shares the thinking behind company direction and strategy.</li>\n<li>A flat organization where you are encouraged to contribute to company direction and strategy.</li>\n<li>The opportunity to help shape the future of data science and machine learning.</li>\n<li>A flexible work environment: work from where you&#39;re most productive.</li>\n<li>Stock in a company that has the potential to transform the way data science is done.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Apply here:\n<a href=\"https://kaggle.applytojob.com/apply/GjSjOi/Fullstack-Engineer?source=Github\">https://kaggle.applytojob.com/apply/GjSjOi/Fullstack-Engineer?source=Github</a></p>\n","company":"Kaggle","company_url":"http://www.kaggle.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/8b90dd46-39df-11e6-9583-738af4d1e73c.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/a0389ac2-39df-11e6-9bb0-7b3faa3729cc"},{"id":"faed66b6-8cad-11e6-9bff-b91f8277615b","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 16:49:14 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Software Engineer - Python Django and Flask","location":"Chicago, IL, US","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><h2><strong>Senior\u00a0Software Engineer -\u00a0Python Django and Flask</strong></h2><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>About This Role:</strong></p><p>The Threadless digital team is building the world&#39;s best platform for artists to share and sell their art.\u00a0We are growing and adding an\u00a0additional Senior Software Engineer to our 9\u00a0person team.\u00a0We work in\u00a0an\u00a0open floor plan office that&#39;s covered in amazing urban\u00a0art,\u00a0in the center of Chicago&#39;s West Loop Neighborhood.</p><p>Threadless is a\u00a0Python shop.\u00a0We&#39;re using\u00a0Django with\u00a0Threadless.com and for our Artist Shops platform. Our API is built on\u00a0top of the Flask framework. To handle our asynchronous work, we have a distributed task\u00a0queue system which has been built with\u00a0Celery.\u00a0We&#39;re an agile team\u00a0that&#39;s focused on enhancing\u00a0Threadless.com and our growing Artist Shops platform.\u00a0Our technology helps\u00a0hundreds of thousands of artists create and sell amazing products\u00a0to\u00a0millions of people.</p><p>If you&#39;re a seasoned\u00a0engineer that&#39;s passionate about coding, solving problems, collaborating, learning, and building\u00a0kick ass products then we&#39;d love to hear from you.</p><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>About Us:</strong></p><p>Threadless is made up of creatives from all over the world who come together to make great art.</p><p>We started with just tees, but tons of products make great canvases. While we work with partners to find these canvases for our artists, it\u2019s our community who makes and picks the best art for us to offer. Whether it\u2019s voted-on art at Threadless.com or designs artists choose to include on their very own Artist Shops, when you buy from us, you support great art. The weird art. The geeky art. The beautiful art.</p><p><em>Threadless. Make Great Together</em></p><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>Education:</strong></p><p>BS in Computer Science, related degree, or equivalent experience</p><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a05+ years experience developing large web applications</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Expertise with Python, Django and Flask\u00a0frameworks preferred</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Experience writing scalable and efficient code for large\u00a0production web applications</p><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>Bonus Points For:</strong></p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Full stack engineering: front end and back end experience</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Django wizardry: implementation of efficient models, killer views, and DRY templates.\u00a0</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Comfortable writing valid and semantic HTML, leveraging CSS pre-processors (SASS specifically), working with JavaScript</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Excellent Git-fu</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Quality contributions to open source projects</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Experience optimizing the performance of web applications</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Hands-on experience refactoring production code</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Basic knowledge of Amazon Web Services, or other cloud hosting services</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Love of\u00a0software engineering practices like: test driven development, continuous integration, pair programming, and code reviews</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Examples of launched projects</p><p>\u00a0</p><p><strong>Perks:</strong></p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Full benefits package and matching 401k plan</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Unlimited vacation policy and flexible schedules, including the ability to work remotely</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0 Paid Maternity and Paternity Leave</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Access to conferences and continued education</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Tons of free Threadless merchandise</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Work\u00a0in a casual environment with talented, innovative people</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 Video games in the office, canine co-workers, table tennis, foosball,\u00a0kegerators, bottomless LaCroix, endless snacks and catered breakfasts\u00a0</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Fitness program reimbursements</p><p>\u00b7 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0Mass transit benefits</p> <img src=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FQZZ\"/></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FQZj\">https://www.applytracking.com/track.aspx/7FQZj</a></p>\n","company":"Threadless","company_url":null,"company_logo":null,"url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/faed66b6-8cad-11e6-9bff-b91f8277615b"},{"id":"149ef362-8caa-11e6-9d71-acd6900f13a8","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 16:21:19 UTC 2016","title":"iOS Ecosystem Developer","location":"Berlin","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><strong>DESCRIPTION</strong></p>\n\n<p>Contentful (<a href=\"https://www.contentful.com\">https://www.contentful.com</a>) is a content management developer platform that enables web and mobile developers to manage, integrate, and deliver digital content to any kind of device or service that can connect to an API - be it smart cars, VR, mobile, web, digital signage, or any new platform. We solve the complexities of content management for tens of thousands web and mobile developers, some independent and many working at enterprise customers that include Jack-in-the-box, Petsmart, Specialized, Fidelity Investments, and Urban Outfitters.   </p>\n\n<p>We&#39;re a fun team of over 75 people from 28 nations with offices in Berlin and San Francisco, backed by top VCs (Benchmark, Trinity, Balderton, Point Nine), growing at an amazing pace, and looking for more amazing individuals to join our team!   </p>\n\n<p>Contentful customers run a wide range of deployments that consume our API. Making the API easy to integrate is fundamental and this role is all about working on Open Source code that other developers will love to use in their applications.   </p>\n\n<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n\n<p>As our iOS Ecosystem Developer you\u2019ll maintain our open source iOS SDK as well as other integrations and example apps.   </p>\n\n<p>You will get to work with the entire range of Apple\u2019s platforms as our SDK also supports macOS, watchOS and tvOS. We are always looking to showcase how Contentful utilizes the latest features and APIs.   </p>\n\n<p>Check out the examples of what we are working on at <a href=\"https://github.com/contentful\">https://github.com/contentful</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/contentful-labs\">https://github.com/contentful-labs</a>   </p>\n\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n\n<p>*You worked on non-trivial iOS projects in Objective-C and Swift<br>\n*You\u2019re active in the iOS community and understand its dynamics and values<br>\n*Solid experience integrating with external REST APIs<br>\n*Strong knowledge of the Cocoa APIs<br>\n*You already participated in Open Source work that you can reference<br>\n*Strong culture for testing and continuous integration<br>\n*You have experience with versioning of libraries, backwards compatibility<br>\n*You can not only build, you can also run it<br>\n*You have passion for new technologies and Apple products<br>\n*Computer Science degree or equivalent experience   </p>\n\n<p><strong>BENEFITS</strong></p>\n\n<p>*The Web and Mobile are changing and becoming more interactive, be part of this revolution and work with *cutting-edge technologies on their future.<br>\n*A majority of your work will be open source.<br>\n*Join a real tech company that counts among its investor and advisors people like Adam Wiggins (Heroku) and Francesco Cesarini (Erlang Solutions).<br>\n*We offer education budget and extra days off to be spent on your self-development.<br>\n*Pick any tools you feel comfortable with. From hardware, to software, to your work environment, we&#39;ve literally got your back.<br>\n*Enjoy the flexibility of time and place of your work.<br>\n*Brush up your language skills! Our team speaks more than 20 languages, and we offer free German classes!\n*We fully support your move to Berlin with a relocation budget. We also get your back in terms of settling down in a new city.</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\"https://contentful.workable.com/jobs/324927\">Apply via link</a></p>\n","company":"Contentful GmbH","company_url":"https://www.contentful.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/12bbbdb4-8caa-11e6-9067-4d74c127da1c.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/149ef362-8caa-11e6-9d71-acd6900f13a8"},{"id":"cbe93ccc-8c95-11e6-822c-85244bcf7366","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 13:58:05 UTC 2016","title":"iOS Developer (Audio)","location":"Berlin","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>We are looking for an iOS Developer as full-time or part-time position in our office in Berlin.</p>\n\n<p>Mimi Hearing Technologies, founded in 2014 in Berlin, is one of the most promising\nstartups in the mHealth / sound space. We develop tools for people to explore their\nhearing health and enjoy a unique listening experience - we strive to be the\nforefront of sound innovation.</p>\n\n<p>Our skills are deeply rooted in science, psychoacoustics and engineering . The Mimi\nteam is a diverse group of innovators with strong expertise in audio- and sound\nengineering, product, communication and business design. </p>\n\n<p><b> Our vision is to set a new standard for the way we listen and become the #1\ntechnology for personalized sound and hearing health.</b></p>\n\n<p>A few facts:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Mimi Hearing Test is the number one hearing test app in the AppStore with\nover one million tested ears worldwide</li>\n<li>Mimi Music is revolutionizing the way, how people listen to Music and the\nupcoming Mimi SDK will enable even more use cases for our technology</li>\n<li>Total number of app downloads: 650K</li>\n<li>Two patents filed + two patents in the pipeline</li>\n<li>Close cooperation with Charit\u00e9 Berlin and medical certification of our products</li>\n<li>Our vision is to set a new standard for the way we listen and become the #1\ntechnology for personalized sound and hearing health.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build advanced applications for the iOS platform optimized for all available\nscreen sizes</li>\n<li>Collaborate with our cross-functional team to define, design, and ship new\nproduct features</li>\n<li>Improve application performance</li>\n<li>Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize\ndevelopment efficiency</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><b>Requirements</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A proven working experience in software development, thereof at least 2-3\nyears in iOS development</li>\n<li>A BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related subject is a plus</li>\n<li>Have published one or more iOS apps in the app store</li>\n<li>A deep familiarity with Objective-C, Swift and Cocoa Touch</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of the iOS platform</li>\n<li>Solid knowledge of software design patterns and system architecture</li>\n<li>Experience with third-party libraries and APIs</li>\n<li>Working knowledge of the general mobile landscape, architectures, trends, and\nemerging technologies</li>\n<li> Experience with REST-API&#39;s</li>\n<li>Fluent in English, good German skills help but are not necessary. Company\nlanguage is English.</li>\n<li>Optional: Experience in C++, Continuous Integration (Jenkins), Backend</li>\n<li>Technologies (NodeJS), realtime audio processing, DSP, Knowledge in\ndeveloping Apple Watch Apps.</li>\n</ul>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>Please send us an email with your CV to <a href=\"mailto:jobs@mimi.io\">jobs@mimi.io</a>.</p>\n","company":"Mimi Hearing Technologies GmbH","company_url":"http://Mimi Hearing Technologies GmbH","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/ede0dee0-8c93-11e6-853c-bf1d64820496.png","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/cbe93ccc-8c95-11e6-822c-85244bcf7366"},{"id":"1d6e90be-8c92-11e6-9cc1-a039aa6674ad","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 13:41:22 UTC 2016","title":"Web Application Developer \u2013 Dept. of Educational Informatics","location":"New York, NY","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>NYU Langone Medical Center, a world-class, patient-centered, integrated, academic medical center, is one of the nation\u2019s premier centers for excellence in clinical care, biomedical research and medical education. Located in the heart of Manhattan, NYU Langone is composed of four hospitals \u2013 Tisch Hospital, its flagship acute care facility; Rusk Rehabilitation; the Hospital for Joint Diseases, one of only five hospitals in the nation dedicated to orthopaedics and rheumatology; and Hassenfeld Children\u2019s Hospital, a comprehensive pediatric hospital supporting a full array of children\u2019s health services across the medical center \u2013 plus the NYU School of Medicine, which since 1841 has trained thousands of physicians and scientists who have helped to shape the course of medical history. The medical center\u2019s tri-fold mission to serve, teach and discover is achieved 365 days a year through the seamless integration of a culture devoted to excellence in patient care, education and research. For more information, go to <a href=\"http://www.NYULMC.org\">www.NYULMC.org</a>.</p>\n\n<p>We have an exciting opportunity to join our team as a Web Application Developer, Dept of Educational Informatics.</p>\n\n<p>Position Summary:\nDEI is the R&amp;D department for educational technology. We\u2019re a team of software engineers and we develop innovative applications and infrastructure for undergraduate, graduate and postgraduate medical education. The applications and programs developed by DEI play an essential role in advancing the educational program of the NYU School of Medicine.</p>\n\n<p>Our technology team is highly collaborative and we are passionate about building and refining our systems, software, and user experience to be as simple, yet as effective as possible. We have a nice new office in Midtown, and we offer one of the best health insurance &amp; benefits packages in New York.</p>\n\n<p>DEI is currently building a unified evaluation platform for all learners, staff, and faculty. In association with the Education Data Warehouse team, we\u2019re using learning and natural language processing to make it easier for humans to analyze thousands of evaluations and other large datasets.</p>\n\n<p>Our stack currently includes Node.js, React, Python, Django, and Java/Grails, Linux, and MySQL.</p>\n\n<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with the technology in our stack or comparable experience</li>\n<li>Experience with a MV* frameworks, RESTful API design, and design patterns.</li>\n<li>Solid fundamental understanding of software development best practices.</li>\n<li>Experience with functional programming. Excellent communication and problem solving skills.</li>\n<li>General programming tasks for the Division of Educational Informatics and other projects as needed. Generally working with a small team of developers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Minimum Qualifications:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Must have a Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science or related discipline and ~2 years of experience.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Preferred Qualifications:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Excellent coding skills (Javascript, Python, Java)</li>\n<li>Knowledge of SQL (MySQL / PostgreSQL / Oracle)</li>\n<li>Experience with Continuous Integration, TDD, and Git</li>\n<li>Familiar with agile software development practices</li>\n<li>Strong data modelling skills</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Linux and basic shell scripting</li>\n<li>Good to know: Node.js, React, Django, Nginx</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Qualified candidates must be able to effectively communicate with all levels of the organization. </p>\n\n<p>For consideration, please apply online at: <a href=\"http://jobs.nyulangone.org/job/6731939/web-application-developer-dept-of-educational-informatics-new-york-ny/\">http://jobs.nyulangone.org/job/6731939/web-application-developer-dept-of-educational-informatics-new-york-ny/</a></p>\n\n<p>NYU Langone Medical Center provides its staff with far more than just a place to work. Rather, we are an institution you can be proud of, an institution where you\u2019ll feel good about devoting your time and your talents. And just as our employees invest so much in us, we invest in our employees. We\u2019re pleased to have one of the most competitive compensation packages not only among New York\u2019s hospitals and healthcare institutions, but within the corporate sector as well. We begin with exceptional medical, dental, and drug coverage. We enhance this basic coverage with comprehensive wellness programs, and supplement those with retirement investment and benefits plans, and generous paid time off allowances. Add to that a very attractive tuition program, and you\u2019ll see just some of the ways that NYU Langone Medical Center demonstrates our commitment to our employees.</p>\n\n<p>EOE including Disabled and Vets VEVRAA Federal Contractor</p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p>For consideration, please apply online at: <a href=\"http://jobs.nyulangone.org/job/6731939/web-application-developer-dept-of-educational-informatics-new-york-ny/\">http://jobs.nyulangone.org/job/6731939/web-application-developer-dept-of-educational-informatics-new-york-ny/</a></p>\n","company":"NYU Langone Medical Center","company_url":"http://jobs.nyulangone.org","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/1638d3f4-8c92-11e6-8c95-311557ec1c86.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/1d6e90be-8c92-11e6-9cc1-a039aa6674ad"},{"id":"1c210922-8c87-11e6-832a-59026ca4dc8d","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 12:12:14 UTC 2016","title":"IT Solutions Developer","location":"Rotterdam","type":"Full Time","description":"<p><I>Samskip is op zoek naar een evenwichtige persoonlijkheid met een can-do-mentaliteit die zelfstandig kan werken, met een proactieve en gedisciplineerde werkhouding!</I><p></p>\n\n<p><B>Wat vragen wij van je?</b><br>\nAls IT Solutions Developer krijg je te maken met een veelzijdige functie met verantwoordelijkheid. Je weet jezelf zodanig te ontwikkelen dat je op termijn advies kunt geven over softwareontwikkelingen op onze softwareplatforms. Kennis van en ervaring met Outsystems is dan ook zeker een pre, evenals kennis van begrippen als AS2, FTP, Mail, http en SOAP. Daarnaast:\n<ul><li>beschik je over een afgeronde hbo opleiding in informatica;\n<li>beheers je de Nederlandse en Engelse taal, in woord en geschrift;\n<li>heb je ervaring met het schrijven van cross-platform interfaces;\n<li>bezit je kennis van EDI-communicatie en maak je gebruik van EDIFACT, XML en ANSI-X12.</ul> <p></p>\n\n<p>Voel jij je aangesproken? Lees dan verder!<p></p>\n\n<p><B>Je functie</b><br>\nJe bent de schakel tussen IT, projectteams en de werkvloer, en assisteert bij gedetailleerd systeemontwerp, codering, testen, gebruikersaanvaarding, implementatie en training. Daarnaast sta je onze teams goed bij op het gebied van Neuron-ESB, SeeBurger, BIS6 en Outsystems, en weet jij je te handhaven binnen het grote Samskip Multimodal IT-Landscape omtrent WebServices, REST, JSON en SSL. Verdere werkzaamheden zijn:\n<ul><li>het ontwikkelen van business-to-business communicatie door middel van EDI-connecties met onze partners (klanten, leveranciers, terminals en autoriteiten);\n<li>het uitvoeren van het daadwerkelijke development;\n<li>het samenwerken met onze softwareleverancier aan onze Digital Transformation, op een agile en scrum methodiek.</ul> <p></p>\n\n<p><B>Wat bieden wij jou?</b><br>\nWerken bij Samskip betekent werken in een ambitieuze, dynamische en professionele werkomgeving. Met jouw servicegerichte werkhouding vervul je een waardevolle rol binnen ons team en draag je bij aan de duurzame groei van Samskip. Daarnaast biedt Samskip je:\n<ul><li>een marktconform salaris, inclusief vakantiegeld en een dertiende maand;\n<li>28 vakantiedagen;\n<li>een pensioenvoorziening;\n<li>een tegemoetkoming in woon-werkverkeer.</ul> <p></p>\n\n<p><b>Ge\u00efnteresseerd?</b><br>\nAls jij graag aan de slag wilt met uitdagende werkzaamheden binnen verschillende softwareprojecten, dan zien we graag je cv en motivatie tegemoet! Klik op <a href=\"https://samskip.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/it_solutions_developer_rotterdam/114881/V819/solliciteren\">deze link</a> en solliciteer direct online.<p></p>\n\n<p><B>Over Samskip</b><br>\nSamskip is een transportbedrijf dat wereldwijd transport en transportgerelateerde services biedt over land, zee, spoor en via de lucht. Wij richten ons in het bijzonder op kosteneffici\u00ebnt, duurzaam en milieuvriendelijk vervoer. Met een omzet van meer dan 625 miljoen euro is Samskip \u00e9\u00e9n van de grootste transportbedrijven binnen Europa, met kantoren in 24 landen in Europa, Noord- en Zuid-Amerika, Azi\u00eb en Australi\u00eb en ongeveer 1400 werknemers in totaal.<p></p>\n\n<p><B><I>Acquisitie naar aanleiding van deze vacature wordt niet op prijs gesteld</b></i> <p></p>\n\n<p><I>Trefwoorden: Vacature, Fulltime, Rotterdam, Software ontwikkelaar, Software engineer.</i></p>\n","how_to_apply":"<p><a href=\" https://samskip.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/it_solutions_developer_rotterdam/114881/V819/solliciteren\">Klik hier voor het sollicitatieformulier!</a></p>\n","company":"Samskip","company_url":"http://www.samskip.com","company_logo":"http://github-jobs.s3.amazonaws.com/53151b22-8c86-11e6-9564-0afb1a522b4c.jpg","url":"http://jobs.github.com/positions/1c210922-8c87-11e6-832a-59026ca4dc8d"},{"id":"350a46e0-8c70-11e6-889f-4b47604c60e4","created_at":"Fri Oct 07 09:27:36 UTC 2016","title":"Senior Developer (m/w)","location":"Cologne","type":"Full Time","description":"<p>Als Teil von ThoughtWorks agilen Projektteams lieferst Du unseren Kunden innovative Software-L\u00f6sungen. Dabei wirst Du eng mit ThoughtWorks Entwicklern, Projektmanagern, Testern, Analysten und Experience Designern zusammenarbeiten, um Ideen kreativ und iterativ in praktische und ma\u00dfgeschneiderte L\u00f6sungen umzusetzen.</p>\n\n<p><strong>DARAUF KANNST DU DICH FREUEN:</strong></p>\n\